WEBVTT

1
00:01:07.625 --> 00:01:09.416
Okay. How about…

2
00:01:09.500 --> 00:01:13.250
a rocket dog with space chips?

3
00:01:14.750 --> 00:01:16.458
Spaghetti with meteors?

4
00:01:18.416 --> 00:01:20.125
Galactic grape cup?

5
00:01:22.791 --> 00:01:24.666
Elio. you have to eat something.

6
00:01:25.958 --> 00:01:28.291
Do you remember what your mom
used to order for you?

7
00:01:32.125 --> 00:01:34.416
Major Solís.
what are you doing here?

8
00:01:34.500 --> 00:01:37.583
Hey! Yeah. I-I'm with my nephew.

9
00:01:37.666 --> 00:01:39.416
I'm trying to get him to eat.

10
00:01:39.500 --> 00:01:42.541
Oh. right. Your nephew.

11
00:01:43.083 --> 00:01:47.166
I heard about your brother
and his wife. I'm so sorry.

12
00:01:47.250 --> 00:01:48.250
Thank you.

13
00:01:49.250 --> 00:01:50.708
We're managing.

14
00:01:50.791 --> 00:01:52.916
What about the astronaut program?

15
00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:55.041
- Weren't you about…
- No. Not anymore.

16
00:01:55.125 --> 00:01:57.666
The. um-- The timing just isn't right.

17
00:01:57.750 --> 00:01:58.750
Of course.

18
00:01:59.333 --> 00:02:00.958
But it's-- But it's been great

19
00:02:01.041 --> 00:02:02.791
spending time with my new roommate.

20
00:02:02.875 --> 00:02:03.875
Right. buddy?

21
00:02:03.958 --> 00:02:05.750
Oh. no.

22
00:02:53.750 --> 00:02:56.666
<i>Hello from</i>
<i>the children of Planet Earth.</i>

23
00:02:59.916 --> 00:03:01.583
<i>Since the dawn of time.</i>

24
00:03:01.666 --> 00:03:04.708
<i>humans have gazed at the stars</i>
<i>and wondered…</i>

25
00:03:05.291 --> 00:03:06.750
<i>are we alone?</i>

26
00:03:07.875 --> 00:03:10.250
Voyager <i>is our attempt to find out.</i>

27
00:03:11.166 --> 00:03:14.125
<i>This intrepid explorer is on a mission.</i>

28
00:03:14.208 --> 00:03:17.875
<i>traveling farther</i>
<i>than any human has ever gone.</i>

29
00:03:17.958 --> 00:03:21.875
<i>to the distant reaches</i>
<i>of the cosmos and beyond.</i>

30
00:03:23.458 --> 00:03:26.958
Voyager <i>will never see those</i>
<i>who made it again.</i>

31
00:03:27.041 --> 00:03:31.083
<i>It will drift on. solitary and alone.</i>

32
00:03:31.916 --> 00:03:33.666
<i>But maybe one day.</i>

33
00:03:33.750 --> 00:03:36.500
<i>distant worlds will receive its message</i>

34
00:03:36.583 --> 00:03:39.125
<i>and Voyager will complete its mission.</i>

35
00:03:39.208 --> 00:03:42.541
<i>proving we aren't so alone after all.</i>

36
00:03:48.500 --> 00:03:50.791
Elio! Elio!

37
00:03:51.291 --> 00:03:53.375
Elio…

38
00:03:53.458 --> 00:03:55.875
Are you-- Are you hurt? What happened?

39
00:03:55.958 --> 00:03:57.083
What happened?

40
00:03:57.166 --> 00:03:59.250
Is life really out there. <i>Tía</i> Olga?

41
00:03:59.333 --> 00:04:00.291
What?

42
00:04:01.833 --> 00:04:02.833
Come on.

43
00:04:03.708 --> 00:04:06.500
You can't run away like that. Elio.

44
00:04:15.750 --> 00:04:17.375
<i>I would like</i>
<i>to extend the greetings</i>

45
00:04:17.458 --> 00:04:19.041
<i>of the government</i>
<i>and the people of Canada.</i>

46
00:04:48.500 --> 00:04:51.583
<i>Hello from</i>
<i>the children of Planet Earth.</i>

47
00:05:28.916 --> 00:05:29.916
Oh. wait.

48
00:05:37.166 --> 00:05:38.166
Okay.

49
00:06:04.916 --> 00:06:05.916
Elio!

50
00:07:01.541 --> 00:07:03.500
Huh?

51
00:07:12.083 --> 00:07:13.500
Hey.

52
00:07:14.958 --> 00:07:16.666
Are you Elio?

53
00:07:16.750 --> 00:07:18.375
Who wants to know?

54
00:07:18.458 --> 00:07:20.750
You put flyers up for a Ham Radio Club?

55
00:07:20.833 --> 00:07:21.875
Uh…

56
00:07:21.958 --> 00:07:24.250
Uh. I-I am Elio Solís.

57
00:07:24.333 --> 00:07:27.541
president and leader of the Ham Radio Club

58
00:07:27.625 --> 00:07:29.416
of this beach.

59
00:07:29.500 --> 00:07:30.666
Cool. I'm Bryce.

60
00:07:30.750 --> 00:07:32.416
Great. cool. awesome. Did you bring it?

61
00:07:32.500 --> 00:07:33.541
Oh-Oh. yeah.

62
00:07:33.625 --> 00:07:36.250
It's my dad's ham radio.
but I have my own call sign.

63
00:07:36.333 --> 00:07:37.916
It's PXLOL…

64
00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:40.708
…which sometimes
makes people I talk to laugh.

65
00:07:41.291 --> 00:07:42.375
How far have you called?

66
00:07:42.458 --> 00:07:44.916
On Friday I talked to…

67
00:07:45.708 --> 00:07:46.875
Ohio.

68
00:07:46.958 --> 00:07:47.833
Oh.

69
00:07:48.333 --> 00:07:51.166
If I can pair these together.
I can double their reach.

70
00:07:51.250 --> 00:07:52.625
Okay. you can go now.

71
00:07:52.708 --> 00:07:54.208
Go? Wait.

72
00:07:54.291 --> 00:07:55.583
Where's everyone else?

73
00:07:55.666 --> 00:07:59.125
Unfortunately. most of our
members came down with. uh…

74
00:07:59.208 --> 00:08:01.166
amnesia and forgot to come.

75
00:08:01.250 --> 00:08:02.958
but I'll see you at the
next meetup in three months!

76
00:08:03.041 --> 00:08:04.458
-What's up. Bryce?
-Hey.

77
00:08:04.541 --> 00:08:06.000
Oh. Oh. Oh.

78
00:08:06.083 --> 00:08:07.833
- One. two…
- Oh.

79
00:08:08.333 --> 00:08:09.541
You almost messed up there.

80
00:08:09.625 --> 00:08:10.625
Hey. Uh…

81
00:08:10.708 --> 00:08:11.916
- Uh-huh.
- Oh.

82
00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:13.166
Oh. yeah.

83
00:08:13.250 --> 00:08:14.750
- Swoosh!
- Nice.

84
00:08:14.833 --> 00:08:16.791
This is Caleb. He wanted to come too.

85
00:08:16.875 --> 00:08:18.583
Oh. Hey.

86
00:08:18.666 --> 00:08:19.833
What's with the hat?

87
00:08:19.916 --> 00:08:21.083
Uh…

88
00:08:21.166 --> 00:08:23.333
Like I said. the meetup's been postponed.

89
00:08:23.416 --> 00:08:24.583
Shingles is no joke.

90
00:08:24.666 --> 00:08:26.166
I thought it was amnesia.

91
00:08:26.250 --> 00:08:28.250
Oh. my gosh. you're right. It's spreading.

92
00:08:28.333 --> 00:08:29.750
You better go before you catch it. Bye!

93
00:08:29.833 --> 00:08:31.750
-Yo. what's up with this guy?
-Dude. chill.

94
00:08:31.833 --> 00:08:33.041
He's the kid whose parents died.

95
00:08:33.125 --> 00:08:34.625
Hey. that's classified information.

96
00:08:34.708 --> 00:08:36.458
As leader of this radio club. I hereby…

97
00:08:39.166 --> 00:08:40.125
-Whoa.
-Did you do that?

98
00:08:40.208 --> 00:08:41.166
Shh. shh. shh.

99
00:08:41.250 --> 00:08:42.083
No.

100
00:08:42.166 --> 00:08:43.875
-Is this supposed to happen?
-Don't. Stop it!

101
00:08:44.541 --> 00:08:46.208
Hello? Hello? Can you hear me?

102
00:08:46.291 --> 00:08:47.541
-Let me see that.
-Don't touch that.

103
00:08:47.625 --> 00:08:50.041
-I was just looking at it.
-I have to respond.

104
00:08:50.125 --> 00:08:50.958
-Let go!
-Quit it.

105
00:08:51.541 --> 00:08:53.083
No!

106
00:08:55.083 --> 00:08:57.708
Yo. that was not my fault.

107
00:08:57.791 --> 00:08:59.041
I-I didn't mean to…

108
00:08:59.125 --> 00:09:00.625
-Uh…
-Oh. come on.

109
00:09:00.708 --> 00:09:02.958
You suborbital. gaseous…

110
00:09:03.041 --> 00:09:04.583
waste of mass!

111
00:09:04.666 --> 00:09:07.041
-Whoa.
-Activate supernova blast!

112
00:09:07.125 --> 00:09:09.250
Get off of me. you little freak.

113
00:09:09.333 --> 00:09:11.375
- Come on. guys. stop!
- He bit me!

114
00:09:11.458 --> 00:09:13.916
Hey. what are you doing?

115
00:09:15.500 --> 00:09:17.625
Unbelievable!

116
00:09:17.708 --> 00:09:20.458
Fighting on the beach. skipping school?

117
00:09:20.541 --> 00:09:22.375
Am I going to have to put
a tracker on you?

118
00:09:23.666 --> 00:09:25.750
Now your eye. <i>Ay Mamá.</i>

119
00:09:25.833 --> 00:09:28.416
The doctor said not
to touch it for two weeks.

120
00:09:28.500 --> 00:09:29.708
-Elio!
-Oh.

121
00:09:29.791 --> 00:09:30.875
You meant starting now.

122
00:09:30.958 --> 00:09:33.500
This is serious! What were you thinking?

123
00:09:33.583 --> 00:09:36.083
I was minding my own business.
taking in the night air

124
00:09:36.166 --> 00:09:37.833
and suddenly these ruffians attacked me.

125
00:09:37.916 --> 00:09:38.958
No. no. no.

126
00:09:39.041 --> 00:09:40.000
Look at me in the eye

127
00:09:40.083 --> 00:09:41.958
and for once. tell me the truth.

128
00:09:45.375 --> 00:09:47.166
No. I'm not learning Elioese.

129
00:09:49.916 --> 00:09:50.875
Major Solís.

130
00:09:50.958 --> 00:09:52.458
You going to the seminar tonight?

131
00:09:52.541 --> 00:09:55.458
There'll be a speaker from the
Astronaut Selection Program.

132
00:09:56.541 --> 00:09:57.875
No. No. no.

133
00:09:57.958 --> 00:09:59.208
Something came up.

134
00:09:59.291 --> 00:10:01.000
Oh. is this the nephew

135
00:10:01.083 --> 00:10:02.083
we've heard so much about?

136
00:10:02.166 --> 00:10:03.250
Yes. that's him.

137
00:10:03.333 --> 00:10:04.666
-<i>Gloodle!</i>
-Stop it!

138
00:10:05.833 --> 00:10:07.666
I don't know if this is boundary testing.

139
00:10:07.750 --> 00:10:09.291
or sleep regression. or…

140
00:10:09.875 --> 00:10:12.000
Which one of these is you?

141
00:10:12.625 --> 00:10:16.000
I don't know. but I think that one is you.

142
00:10:18.666 --> 00:10:20.916
Okay. I've got one last meeting.

143
00:10:21.000 --> 00:10:22.875
So. I need you to sit here

144
00:10:22.958 --> 00:10:24.583
and not move or speak

145
00:10:24.666 --> 00:10:27.083
or injure yourself for ten minutes.

146
00:10:29.708 --> 00:10:31.916
I have enough to deal with already.

147
00:10:37.000 --> 00:10:38.291
What's with
this emergency meeting?

148
00:10:38.375 --> 00:10:39.500
Oh. you didn't hear?

149
00:10:39.583 --> 00:10:41.666
Melmac thinks he found aliens.

150
00:10:41.750 --> 00:10:44.000
This ought to be good.

151
00:10:48.625 --> 00:10:50.666
All right. Mr. Melmac. let's hear it.

152
00:10:51.333 --> 00:10:52.958
Major…

153
00:10:53.041 --> 00:10:54.541
Major Solís. earlier today.

154
00:10:54.625 --> 00:10:57.625
I found this signal coming
from interstellar space.

155
00:11:08.666 --> 00:11:09.916
Melmac. please.

156
00:11:10.000 --> 00:11:11.500
-It's late…
-Wait. wait. wait.

157
00:11:11.583 --> 00:11:13.083
Listen closely.

158
00:11:15.208 --> 00:11:17.041
<i>Hello. Planet Earth.</i>

159
00:11:17.125 --> 00:11:19.416
<i>Hello. Planet Earth.</i>

160
00:11:19.500 --> 00:11:21.500
In 1977. NASA launched the…

161
00:11:21.583 --> 00:11:23.083
-The Golden Record.
-The Golden Record! Yes.

162
00:11:23.166 --> 00:11:26.208
-The what?
-The Golden Record. sir.

163
00:11:26.291 --> 00:11:27.791
was Earth's message in a bottle.

164
00:11:27.875 --> 00:11:30.458
<i>Hello from</i>
<i>the children of Planet Earth.</i>

165
00:11:30.541 --> 00:11:31.541
Don't you see?

166
00:11:31.625 --> 00:11:33.333
<i>Hello. Planet Earth.</i>

167
00:11:33.416 --> 00:11:35.125
I think someone in interstellar space

168
00:11:35.208 --> 00:11:37.125
found our message
and is sending it back to us

169
00:11:37.208 --> 00:11:38.208
as a reply!

170
00:11:39.041 --> 00:11:40.291
-Melmac…
-Major…

171
00:11:40.375 --> 00:11:41.750
-Melmac…
-Major!

172
00:11:41.833 --> 00:11:44.291
We can't just leave it
like this. we have to respond.

173
00:11:44.375 --> 00:11:46.041
I've already rerouted every satellite

174
00:11:46.125 --> 00:11:47.125
to send the signal back.

175
00:11:47.208 --> 00:11:49.083
Sure. it might cause
a few system failures.

176
00:11:49.166 --> 00:11:51.083
Whoop. Sorry.
Maybe a small electrical fire.

177
00:11:51.166 --> 00:11:54.583
but it would be worth it
for first contact!

178
00:11:56.291 --> 00:11:57.833
I have everything cued up and ready to go.

179
00:11:57.916 --> 00:11:59.500
Just say the word!

180
00:11:59.583 --> 00:12:03.291
If someone or something
is calling out to Earth.

181
00:12:03.375 --> 00:12:06.625
who on Earth do you want taking that call?

182
00:12:11.458 --> 00:12:12.875
You…

183
00:12:12.958 --> 00:12:14.500
-…should go home.
-Oh.

184
00:12:14.583 --> 00:12:16.208
- Take a week.
- Take two weeks.

185
00:12:16.291 --> 00:12:17.291
No. You got to believe me.

186
00:12:17.375 --> 00:12:18.875
Major. please! They're out there!

187
00:12:18.958 --> 00:12:20.125
Major! Unhand me!

188
00:12:20.208 --> 00:12:24.500
May I remind everyone
that we are orbital analysts.

189
00:12:24.583 --> 00:12:27.791
We track space debris.
not rogue UFO signals.

190
00:12:28.500 --> 00:12:30.916
Let's just…

191
00:12:31.416 --> 00:12:32.708
Let's just take five.

192
00:12:32.791 --> 00:12:34.000
It's been a long night.

193
00:12:34.083 --> 00:12:36.250
What a nutjob.

194
00:12:50.583 --> 00:12:54.208
This is Elio Solís
of the planet Earth. Uh…

195
00:12:54.708 --> 00:12:56.791
I come in peace…

196
00:12:56.875 --> 00:12:59.583
and I'm super excited to join you. Uh…

197
00:12:59.666 --> 00:13:01.750
I'm creative. hardworking…

198
00:13:02.625 --> 00:13:03.875
shredded.

199
00:13:03.958 --> 00:13:05.958
Uh. so please come and get me.
I'll be waiting.

200
00:13:06.041 --> 00:13:07.166
Okay. bye. Love you.

201
00:13:10.791 --> 00:13:11.916
Yes.

202
00:13:13.125 --> 00:13:14.250
Yes!

203
00:13:15.833 --> 00:13:16.791
Yes!

204
00:13:24.958 --> 00:13:26.041
Oh. no.

205
00:13:26.125 --> 00:13:28.500
Time is of the essence.
They could be here any minute.

206
00:13:28.583 --> 00:13:29.458
I got to pack!

207
00:13:29.541 --> 00:13:30.708
I take full responsibility.

208
00:13:30.791 --> 00:13:32.875
but… …I mean.
you have kids. right?

209
00:13:32.958 --> 00:13:34.458
I'll be out of your way soon. Don't worry.

210
00:13:34.541 --> 00:13:35.791
Just need a few snacks for the road.

211
00:13:35.875 --> 00:13:36.708
Elio!

212
00:13:36.791 --> 00:13:37.750
Sorry. ma'am. What was that?

213
00:13:37.833 --> 00:13:39.375
Which flavor will you
miss the least? <i>¿Fuego?</i>

214
00:13:39.458 --> 00:13:40.458
-<i>Fuego</i>. Yeah.
-I-I understand.

215
00:13:40.541 --> 00:13:42.458
Should I bring forks. or would
they think they're weapons?

216
00:13:42.541 --> 00:13:44.333
Not worth the risk! I'll bring spoons.

217
00:13:44.416 --> 00:13:46.416
Nice. peaceful spoons.

218
00:13:46.500 --> 00:13:48.083
-Where's my good cape?
-You too. ma'am.

219
00:13:48.166 --> 00:13:49.750
-It's not in the wash. is it?
-Thank you.

220
00:13:50.250 --> 00:13:51.541
-Ah. Here it is!
-Elio…

221
00:13:51.625 --> 00:13:53.791
Blue or green? Which one says.
"Take me with you."

222
00:13:53.875 --> 00:13:54.875
but not in a desperate way?

223
00:13:54.958 --> 00:13:56.291
Elio. stop! Please!

224
00:13:58.333 --> 00:14:00.375
Aliens are not coming for you.

225
00:14:01.541 --> 00:14:02.625
But that guy said…

226
00:14:02.708 --> 00:14:04.791
You're out of control. You got in a fight.

227
00:14:04.875 --> 00:14:07.083
You shut down power to the whole base

228
00:14:07.166 --> 00:14:09.083
and I almost lost my job!

229
00:14:11.833 --> 00:14:13.916
We have to try something different.

230
00:14:15.625 --> 00:14:17.291
Boarding school? You're trying
to get rid of me.

231
00:14:17.375 --> 00:14:19.708
No. this is just their sleepaway camp.

232
00:14:19.791 --> 00:14:20.791
It's just a couple of weeks.

233
00:14:20.875 --> 00:14:22.166
I can't go. They're coming tonight.

234
00:14:22.250 --> 00:14:24.875
You need to make friends or just a friend.

235
00:14:24.958 --> 00:14:27.166
I don't care about friends.
I need to meet aliens.

236
00:14:27.250 --> 00:14:28.250
Why?

237
00:14:28.333 --> 00:14:31.000
Because there's 500 million
habitable planets out there

238
00:14:31.083 --> 00:14:32.541
and one of them's got to want me!

239
00:14:32.625 --> 00:14:34.291
Because obviously you don't!

240
00:14:34.375 --> 00:14:36.250
Of course. I do! We're family!

241
00:14:36.333 --> 00:14:37.958
You're not my family!

242
00:14:49.708 --> 00:14:51.416
Your life isn't up there. Elio.

243
00:14:52.625 --> 00:14:53.958
It's down here.

244
00:15:12.291 --> 00:15:14.458
I-I can't deal with this.

245
00:15:14.541 --> 00:15:16.833
I don't know if anybody
can deal with this.

246
00:15:19.250 --> 00:15:20.458
When I drop him off tomorrow.

247
00:15:20.541 --> 00:15:22.583
I'm going to see if they can
enroll him in the fall.

248
00:15:23.750 --> 00:15:24.750
I know.

249
00:15:24.833 --> 00:15:29.666
but this just isn't how
I thought my life would be.

250
00:15:33.958 --> 00:15:35.458
<i>It's an ancient human theme.</i>

251
00:15:35.541 --> 00:15:37.625
<i>You can find it</i>
<i>in virtually every culture.</i>

252
00:15:37.708 --> 00:15:40.125
<i>in. uh. religion. folklore. superstition</i>

253
00:15:40.208 --> 00:15:41.375
<i>and now in science.</i>

254
00:15:42.583 --> 00:15:46.458
<i>The search for life elsewhere</i>
<i>is remarkable in our age.</i>

255
00:15:46.541 --> 00:15:47.875
<i>because this is the first time</i>

256
00:15:47.958 --> 00:15:51.041
<i>that we can actually do</i>
<i>something besides speculation.</i>

257
00:15:52.125 --> 00:15:54.375
<i>We can send spacecraft to nearby planets.</i>

258
00:15:55.791 --> 00:15:57.416
<i>We can use large radio telescopes</i>

259
00:15:57.500 --> 00:16:01.125
<i>to see if there is any message</i>
<i>being sent to us lately…</i>

260
00:16:02.041 --> 00:16:05.375
<i>and it touches to the deepest</i>
<i>of human concerns.</i>

261
00:16:06.708 --> 00:16:07.833
<i>Are we alone?</i>

262
00:16:28.541 --> 00:16:30.083
No contact! No contact!

263
00:16:31.083 --> 00:16:34.000
You know I went here.
too. when I was a kid.

264
00:16:34.875 --> 00:16:36.625
You might not believe me right now…

265
00:16:37.958 --> 00:16:39.375
but this will be good for you.

266
00:16:45.708 --> 00:16:46.541
Oh.

267
00:16:46.625 --> 00:16:48.291
Counselor Truman. could I have a word?

268
00:16:48.375 --> 00:16:49.500
Of course. Major.

269
00:16:55.166 --> 00:16:57.958
We got in so much trouble…

270
00:16:59.000 --> 00:17:00.291
because of you.

271
00:17:00.375 --> 00:17:01.458
Yeah. Thanks a lot.

272
00:17:02.708 --> 00:17:04.125
Better watch your back.

273
00:17:04.208 --> 00:17:05.333
Yeah.

274
00:17:14.166 --> 00:17:15.166
Ugh.

275
00:17:18.333 --> 00:17:19.791
He's going to be so freaked out!

276
00:17:19.875 --> 00:17:21.583
Shh. Follow my lead.

277
00:17:21.666 --> 00:17:23.000
Shh. shh.

278
00:17:23.083 --> 00:17:24.500
Quiet. Quiet.

279
00:17:24.583 --> 00:17:25.916
We're not going to hurt him. right?

280
00:17:26.000 --> 00:17:27.916
-Just scare him a little?
-Come on. it'll be funny.

281
00:17:30.416 --> 00:17:32.166
Shut up! You'll wake him up.

282
00:17:32.250 --> 00:17:34.125
- Come on.
- Quiet. quiet!

283
00:17:34.208 --> 00:17:35.583
Shh. shh. shh.

284
00:17:37.083 --> 00:17:38.583
Greetings. Earthling.

285
00:17:38.666 --> 00:17:40.375
We come in peace!

286
00:17:41.625 --> 00:17:42.708
Where did he go?

287
00:17:49.125 --> 00:17:51.291
<i>Athena 5</i>. there is
a decommissioned satellite

288
00:17:51.375 --> 00:17:52.416
headed your way.

289
00:17:52.500 --> 00:17:54.958
I'm calculating a new
flight path for you. Standby.

290
00:17:55.041 --> 00:17:56.541
<i>Go ahead. Montez.</i>

291
00:17:56.625 --> 00:17:58.958
Minus 53. plus 32. roll seven.

292
00:17:59.041 --> 00:18:00.416
<i>Yeah. copy that.</i>

293
00:18:02.000 --> 00:18:03.083
Sorry about the scare.

294
00:18:03.166 --> 00:18:05.208
There's been a lot of
satellite interference today.

295
00:18:05.291 --> 00:18:07.541
<i>Roger that.</i>
Athena 5<i>. over and out.</i>

296
00:18:42.583 --> 00:18:43.958
Uh…

297
00:18:50.875 --> 00:18:52.458
Elio!

298
00:18:52.541 --> 00:18:54.125
Come out. come out. wherever you are!

299
00:18:54.208 --> 00:18:55.208
Elio!

300
00:18:55.291 --> 00:18:56.333
Don't you want to
hang out with us?

301
00:18:56.416 --> 00:18:57.791
I thought you wanted
to meet some aliens.

302
00:18:57.875 --> 00:18:59.458
Come on. it'll be fun.

303
00:19:02.041 --> 00:19:03.708
He's out here somewhere.

304
00:19:04.208 --> 00:19:06.916
Come on. Space Boy!
We know you're out there.

305
00:19:48.750 --> 00:19:49.750
Hmm?

306
00:19:53.041 --> 00:19:54.083
Gotcha!

307
00:19:54.166 --> 00:19:56.000
Yeah… You found me.

308
00:19:56.083 --> 00:19:57.083
This is payback.

309
00:19:57.166 --> 00:19:59.458
Eh. it's okay.
You don't need to pay me back.

310
00:19:59.541 --> 00:20:01.666
Wait. What is that?

311
00:20:02.458 --> 00:20:04.208
Hope you like how it tastes.

312
00:20:04.291 --> 00:20:05.458
There's something back there.

313
00:20:05.541 --> 00:20:06.875
-Look!
-Argh!

314
00:20:08.166 --> 00:20:09.791
You're so dead. Solís.

315
00:20:09.875 --> 00:20:11.208
Hey. hold on.

316
00:20:12.041 --> 00:20:13.000
Wait.

317
00:21:06.666 --> 00:21:07.875
Please.

318
00:21:13.666 --> 00:21:15.041
Yes!

319
00:21:15.125 --> 00:21:16.583
Yes!

320
00:21:17.791 --> 00:21:20.208
It's happening! It's really happening.

321
00:21:21.583 --> 00:21:23.541
I knew it! I knew it!

322
00:21:23.625 --> 00:21:25.416
Yes!

323
00:21:26.041 --> 00:21:27.916
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

324
00:21:28.000 --> 00:21:31.208
Yes. yes. yes! Yes. yes. yes!

325
00:21:35.833 --> 00:21:37.541
Whoa-ho-ho-ho-ho!

326
00:21:39.083 --> 00:21:41.166
Thank you!

327
00:21:47.375 --> 00:21:49.791
Yes! Yeah!

328
00:21:51.125 --> 00:21:52.000
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

329
00:21:52.083 --> 00:21:53.125
Oh!

330
00:22:01.041 --> 00:22:02.083
Wow.

331
00:22:04.416 --> 00:22:05.416
Hi.

332
00:22:07.166 --> 00:22:08.166
I knew it!

333
00:22:08.250 --> 00:22:11.416
I knew aliens were looking
for me. You saved my life!

334
00:22:11.500 --> 00:22:14.791
I promise I'll pull my weight
on this. uh… spaceship?

335
00:22:14.875 --> 00:22:17.500
Is this a spaceship?
Anyway. where should we start?

336
00:22:17.583 --> 00:22:18.666
Probes? Samples?

337
00:22:18.750 --> 00:22:20.000
I've got plenty.

338
00:22:24.750 --> 00:22:25.750
Testing. testing…

339
00:22:25.833 --> 00:22:26.833
testing.

340
00:22:26.916 --> 00:22:28.666
Can you understand me now?

341
00:22:28.750 --> 00:22:29.916
Yes. Wow.

342
00:22:30.000 --> 00:22:31.250
It is a pleasure to meet you.

343
00:22:31.333 --> 00:22:34.958
I am Ooooo. a liquid supercomputer.

344
00:22:35.041 --> 00:22:36.625
Allow me to adjust your gravity.

345
00:22:36.708 --> 00:22:38.583
-Oh. no. no. no. I'm fine.
-Gravity on.

346
00:22:42.125 --> 00:22:43.666
A welcome glass of glorp.

347
00:22:43.750 --> 00:22:45.375
compliments of the Communiverse.

348
00:22:45.458 --> 00:22:47.458
Oh! Thank you.

349
00:22:47.541 --> 00:22:48.833
Wait. The what?

350
00:22:48.916 --> 00:22:50.083
Whoa.

351
00:23:04.958 --> 00:23:07.291
Welcome to the Communiverse.

352
00:23:07.375 --> 00:23:08.500
a pangalactic organization

353
00:23:08.583 --> 00:23:10.625
of the advanced species of the cosmos.

354
00:23:10.708 --> 00:23:11.583
Whoa.

355
00:23:11.666 --> 00:23:13.791
The greatest minds
of the universe come here

356
00:23:13.875 --> 00:23:15.541
to share knowledge. innovation…

357
00:23:15.625 --> 00:23:17.458
And recipes!

358
00:23:17.541 --> 00:23:18.416
Welcome!

359
00:23:18.500 --> 00:23:19.541
-Welcome.
-Lovely.

360
00:23:19.625 --> 00:23:21.541
Greetings. Ambassadors!

361
00:23:21.625 --> 00:23:24.750
Absolutely ecstatic
to make your acquaintance.

362
00:23:24.833 --> 00:23:28.416
Oop. You've run dry.
Let me top you off. old brick.

363
00:23:28.500 --> 00:23:30.125
Huh. Thank you.

364
00:23:30.208 --> 00:23:33.625
Hmm. yes. One cerebellum. four lobes.

365
00:23:33.708 --> 00:23:36.041
and… a medulla.

366
00:23:36.125 --> 00:23:38.333
Do you mind if I take
a little peek inside and see?

367
00:23:38.416 --> 00:23:41.375
Questa. don't mindread him.
you've just met him.

368
00:23:41.458 --> 00:23:43.166
So sorry about that.

369
00:23:43.250 --> 00:23:45.833
I am Questa of Gom.

370
00:23:45.916 --> 00:23:48.250
Helix of Falluvinum. Mwah.

371
00:23:48.333 --> 00:23:49.625
Tegmen of Tegmeg.

372
00:23:49.708 --> 00:23:51.000
And you are?

373
00:23:52.250 --> 00:23:56.333
Elio Solís of. uh… Earth!

374
00:23:56.416 --> 00:24:00.625
A toast to our new candidate.
Elio Solís of Uh-Earth.

375
00:24:02.833 --> 00:24:04.166
- There he is!
- Elio Solís!

376
00:24:04.250 --> 00:24:05.416
Look. it's Elio!

377
00:24:05.500 --> 00:24:06.583
It's a new candidate.

378
00:24:07.166 --> 00:24:08.583
Salutations!

379
00:24:08.666 --> 00:24:09.625
I love your eye!

380
00:24:10.625 --> 00:24:12.208
We search the universe

381
00:24:12.291 --> 00:24:14.958
for like-minded souls and new species.

382
00:24:15.041 --> 00:24:17.250
and we think you're an excellent candidate

383
00:24:17.333 --> 00:24:19.333
for Communiverse membership.

384
00:24:20.166 --> 00:24:21.833
You mean I could stay here?

385
00:24:21.916 --> 00:24:24.750
If all the members agree. then. yes.

386
00:24:24.833 --> 00:24:29.625
You'll be one of us and be the
proud bearer of one of these.

387
00:24:30.291 --> 00:24:33.000
Now come. everyone's eager to meet you.

388
00:24:39.708 --> 00:24:40.791
Each of us brings

389
00:24:40.875 --> 00:24:43.583
our specialized knowledge
and interest to share.

390
00:24:43.666 --> 00:24:44.750
Greetings. Naos!

391
00:24:44.833 --> 00:24:46.166
Hello. Salutations.

392
00:24:46.250 --> 00:24:49.041
Naos. here. created
the Communidiscs we all use

393
00:24:49.125 --> 00:24:50.750
with controls for gravity…

394
00:24:53.208 --> 00:24:55.208
…temperature…

395
00:24:55.291 --> 00:24:57.208
…and all known languages.

396
00:24:57.291 --> 00:24:59.708
You know Elioese?

397
00:25:06.291 --> 00:25:07.125
-<i>Gloodle</i>.
-<i>Gloodle</i>.

398
00:25:07.208 --> 00:25:08.333
<i>Gloodle</i>!

399
00:25:08.416 --> 00:25:11.875
This is my most recent design. Try it.

400
00:25:11.958 --> 00:25:15.500
Hello. I am the Universal Users Manual.

401
00:25:15.583 --> 00:25:18.083
I contain the secrets of the universe.

402
00:25:18.166 --> 00:25:20.125
What is the meaning of life?

403
00:25:20.208 --> 00:25:23.166
What lies beyond a black hole?
Is there a purpose to…

404
00:25:23.250 --> 00:25:24.208
Who would win in a fight?

405
00:25:24.291 --> 00:25:26.750
One gorilla with
a baseball bat or ten chimps?

406
00:25:26.833 --> 00:25:29.791
None who fight are true winners.

407
00:25:30.416 --> 00:25:31.250
Huh?

408
00:25:32.916 --> 00:25:33.916
The gorilla.

409
00:25:34.000 --> 00:25:35.833
Wow.

410
00:25:36.500 --> 00:25:39.125
These little critters are mimollusks.

411
00:25:39.208 --> 00:25:42.625
They use nanotechnology to
construct anything you desire.

412
00:25:48.500 --> 00:25:49.916
Are you kidding me?

413
00:25:50.000 --> 00:25:51.500
How dashing!

414
00:25:53.791 --> 00:25:56.250
This is the most beautiful place

415
00:25:56.333 --> 00:25:57.791
I've ever seen.

416
00:25:57.875 --> 00:25:59.375
This is the bathroom.

417
00:26:00.458 --> 00:26:02.208
Whee!

418
00:26:04.000 --> 00:26:05.875
- Gets me every time.
- Bracing.

419
00:26:06.875 --> 00:26:09.333
It's like I was always meant to be here.

420
00:26:09.916 --> 00:26:11.583
I knew you were looking for me.

421
00:26:11.666 --> 00:26:13.541
Of course we were looking for you.

422
00:26:13.625 --> 00:26:14.625
Ever since we picked up

423
00:26:14.708 --> 00:26:17.333
this charming little
spacecraft you sent us.

424
00:26:20.250 --> 00:26:21.791
<i>Voyager</i>?

425
00:26:21.875 --> 00:26:23.750
We found it in an asteroid field.

426
00:26:23.833 --> 00:26:25.625
Nice craftsmanship.

427
00:26:25.708 --> 00:26:27.708
Um… thanks?

428
00:26:32.541 --> 00:26:34.375
Curious about
the species who made it.

429
00:26:34.458 --> 00:26:36.000
we sent an invitation

430
00:26:36.083 --> 00:26:39.541
and were delighted to receive
your planet's official reply.

431
00:26:40.208 --> 00:26:42.625
<i>This is Elio Solís</i>
<i>of the planet Earth</i>

432
00:26:42.708 --> 00:26:44.916
<i>and I'm super excited to join you.</i>

433
00:26:45.000 --> 00:26:47.833
<i>I'm creative. hard-working. shredded!</i>

434
00:26:49.166 --> 00:26:50.291
<i>So. please come and get me.</i>
<i>I'll be waiting.</i>

435
00:26:50.375 --> 00:26:51.666
<i>Okay. bye. Love you.</i>

436
00:26:51.750 --> 00:26:53.833
- Very touching.
- We are delighted

437
00:26:53.916 --> 00:26:56.041
to finally make your acquaintance.

438
00:26:56.125 --> 00:26:58.416
Leader of Uh-Earth.

439
00:27:00.250 --> 00:27:01.250
Ooh.

440
00:27:01.333 --> 00:27:02.166
Uh…

441
00:27:02.250 --> 00:27:03.833
Why is your face melting?

442
00:27:03.916 --> 00:27:04.791
Um…

443
00:27:04.875 --> 00:27:06.000
-Well…
-Ambassadors.

444
00:27:06.083 --> 00:27:08.000
an urgent matter requires your attention.

445
00:27:08.083 --> 00:27:09.708
It involves the other candidate.

446
00:27:09.791 --> 00:27:11.166
- Oh. him.
- Oh. dear.

447
00:27:11.250 --> 00:27:12.583
We should hurry. Quickly now!

448
00:27:12.666 --> 00:27:13.666
Excuse us.

449
00:27:16.250 --> 00:27:17.583
Please join us.

450
00:27:22.833 --> 00:27:24.875
Your technology and my weapons

451
00:27:24.958 --> 00:27:27.125
would be an unstoppable alliance.

452
00:27:27.875 --> 00:27:29.875
Now. admit me to your Communiverse!

453
00:27:32.625 --> 00:27:34.583
Unfortunately. Candidate Grigon.

454
00:27:34.666 --> 00:27:36.875
it is our assessment that you are

455
00:27:36.958 --> 00:27:38.041
not a fit.

456
00:27:38.125 --> 00:27:40.208
I. Lord Grigon.

457
00:27:40.291 --> 00:27:44.708
Blood Emperor of Hylurg. not a fit?

458
00:27:45.458 --> 00:27:49.166
Well. we believe in tolerance
and open-mindedness…

459
00:27:49.666 --> 00:27:51.583
I am tolerant!

460
00:27:51.666 --> 00:27:54.208
So sorry. it's not you.

461
00:27:54.291 --> 00:27:55.875
it's us.

462
00:27:57.291 --> 00:27:58.791
I thought we said it was him.

463
00:27:58.875 --> 00:27:59.708
Shh!

464
00:27:59.791 --> 00:28:02.416
If I cannot join the Communiverse.

465
00:28:02.500 --> 00:28:05.416
then I shall take it by force!

466
00:28:05.500 --> 00:28:07.541
Prepare to be conquered!

467
00:28:11.125 --> 00:28:12.250
What a brute!

468
00:28:12.333 --> 00:28:13.583
Why did he make a new hole?

469
00:28:13.666 --> 00:28:15.208
I suggest we run and hide.

470
00:28:15.291 --> 00:28:16.875
Yes. let's go to the edge of the cosmos

471
00:28:16.958 --> 00:28:18.208
and turn off all the lights.

472
00:28:18.291 --> 00:28:21.000
Uh. that includes me. right?

473
00:28:21.083 --> 00:28:23.208
Oh. so sorry. candidate Solís.

474
00:28:23.291 --> 00:28:25.958
we couldn't possibly accept new members

475
00:28:26.041 --> 00:28:27.625
under the current situation.

476
00:28:27.708 --> 00:28:29.666
Applications are closed indefinitely.

477
00:28:29.750 --> 00:28:31.416
- But I just got here!
- Such a shame.

478
00:28:31.500 --> 00:28:34.125
Let's check back in a few thousand years?

479
00:28:34.208 --> 00:28:35.875
Perhaps one of us
could talk to Lord Grigon.

480
00:28:35.958 --> 00:28:36.958
-You do it!
-Not me.

481
00:28:37.041 --> 00:28:38.833
-I am shy.
-I'm busy.

482
00:28:38.916 --> 00:28:40.666
- I have allergies.
- My battery is low.

483
00:28:40.750 --> 00:28:43.291
Don't worry. I'll return you
to your life on Uh-Earth

484
00:28:43.375 --> 00:28:45.583
just as it was… was. was. was…

485
00:28:46.125 --> 00:28:47.500
<i>Just as it was…</i>

486
00:28:48.291 --> 00:28:50.708
No. no!

487
00:28:52.041 --> 00:28:53.041
I'll do it.

488
00:28:55.541 --> 00:28:56.875
I'm the leader of Earth.

489
00:28:57.416 --> 00:28:59.333
I'm the perfect guy for the job.

490
00:29:00.041 --> 00:29:01.125
What did it say?

491
00:29:01.208 --> 00:29:02.583
- How curious.
- I do not understand.

492
00:29:02.666 --> 00:29:04.125
You would talk to Lord Grigon?

493
00:29:04.208 --> 00:29:05.083
But what would you say?

494
00:29:05.166 --> 00:29:07.541
Are you an expert on conflict negotiation?

495
00:29:07.625 --> 00:29:08.875
You kidding?

496
00:29:08.958 --> 00:29:11.583
My life is nothing but conflict

497
00:29:11.666 --> 00:29:14.458
and I've got the battle scars to prove it.

498
00:29:16.333 --> 00:29:18.416
It would be a welcome change

499
00:29:18.500 --> 00:29:21.833
not to flee every bully
who covets our treasures.

500
00:29:24.708 --> 00:29:25.916
Yes. What's in it for you?

501
00:29:26.000 --> 00:29:28.875
Why would you agree
to such a dangerous mission?

502
00:29:29.541 --> 00:29:30.541
Because…

503
00:29:31.083 --> 00:29:32.083
you need me.

504
00:29:32.916 --> 00:29:36.791
And at my age.
it's really about giving back.

505
00:29:36.875 --> 00:29:39.208
If you can make Grigon go away.

506
00:29:39.291 --> 00:29:41.333
we'd make you a member on the spot.

507
00:29:42.416 --> 00:29:45.791
Then I. the leader of Earth.
am ready to serve.

508
00:29:45.875 --> 00:29:47.250
- Good. Very good.
- How impressive!

509
00:29:47.333 --> 00:29:49.125
- What courage!
- Wonderful!

510
00:29:49.208 --> 00:29:52.333
Candidate Solís. you continue to surprise.

511
00:29:52.416 --> 00:29:55.750
When Grigon returns.
we shall be ready for him.

512
00:29:55.833 --> 00:29:58.375
Until then. as you say on Uh-Earth.

513
00:29:58.458 --> 00:30:00.500
Okay. bye. I love you.

514
00:30:00.583 --> 00:30:02.916
Okay. Bye. I love you.

515
00:30:03.000 --> 00:30:04.666
Don't worry. I got this.

516
00:30:04.750 --> 00:30:06.458
You're in great hands.

517
00:30:09.750 --> 00:30:11.166
Just one last order of business.

518
00:30:11.250 --> 00:30:12.833
Oh. yeah. of course.

519
00:30:14.083 --> 00:30:15.791
While you negotiate with the warlord.

520
00:30:15.875 --> 00:30:17.166
you'll need a temporary replacement.

521
00:30:17.250 --> 00:30:18.083
Whoa.

522
00:30:18.166 --> 00:30:20.166
Can I trouble you
for a DNA sample?

523
00:30:20.250 --> 00:30:21.708
Sure. Where do you want it… Argh!

524
00:30:22.916 --> 00:30:24.666
Yeow!

525
00:30:30.208 --> 00:30:32.541
Wow. My first probe.

526
00:30:34.083 --> 00:30:35.791
World leaders. such as yourself.

527
00:30:35.875 --> 00:30:37.083
can't just disappear.

528
00:30:37.166 --> 00:30:39.416
Your planet would descend into chaos.

529
00:30:40.541 --> 00:30:42.791
That's what cloning clay is for.

530
00:30:49.000 --> 00:30:49.875
Whoa.

531
00:31:03.333 --> 00:31:04.541
Whoa.

532
00:31:06.875 --> 00:31:07.833
Is this…?

533
00:31:07.916 --> 00:31:09.416
Are you…?

534
00:31:09.500 --> 00:31:10.333
Me?

535
00:31:11.333 --> 00:31:12.250
Rock…

536
00:31:12.333 --> 00:31:13.250
Paper…

537
00:31:13.333 --> 00:31:14.541
Black hole! Oh!

538
00:31:15.416 --> 00:31:17.375
-Space is the best!
-Space is amazing!

539
00:31:21.583 --> 00:31:22.708
In you go.

540
00:31:22.791 --> 00:31:23.875
Sorry.

541
00:31:23.958 --> 00:31:25.083
It's a living.

542
00:31:25.166 --> 00:31:26.791
So. what is my motivation?

543
00:31:26.875 --> 00:31:27.958
What do you mean?

544
00:31:28.041 --> 00:31:29.625
Should I change anything

545
00:31:29.708 --> 00:31:31.291
or just stick with the low self-esteem

546
00:31:31.375 --> 00:31:32.333
and desperation to belong?

547
00:31:32.416 --> 00:31:35.583
What? I'm normal. just be normal.

548
00:31:35.666 --> 00:31:37.000
No weird stuff. okay?

549
00:31:37.083 --> 00:31:38.708
-Okay.
-Okay.

550
00:31:45.791 --> 00:31:46.791
Have fun.

551
00:31:47.791 --> 00:31:51.041
Intriguing Uh-Earth custom.
The warlord awaits.

552
00:31:51.125 --> 00:31:53.500
Oh. uh. there was. uh. just a few things

553
00:31:53.583 --> 00:31:54.916
I wanted to brush up on.

554
00:31:55.000 --> 00:31:56.625
Where was that thing that knew
everything about everything?

555
00:31:56.708 --> 00:31:57.708
You mean this?

556
00:31:57.791 --> 00:32:00.875
Hello. I am the Universal Users Manual.

557
00:32:00.958 --> 00:32:03.833
Would you like to learn the
meaning of life now? It's a…

558
00:32:03.916 --> 00:32:04.916
No. I need everything you've got

559
00:32:05.000 --> 00:32:06.583
on how to negotiate with the warmonger.

560
00:32:08.208 --> 00:32:09.541
Certainly.

561
00:32:09.625 --> 00:32:11.666
I have chapters on leading with empathy.

562
00:32:11.750 --> 00:32:12.583
Nope.

563
00:32:12.666 --> 00:32:13.958
- Fostering connection?
- Nope.

564
00:32:14.041 --> 00:32:15.583
Making the killer deal?

565
00:32:15.666 --> 00:32:17.375
Yes. that one. Do you have a pen?

566
00:32:17.458 --> 00:32:20.291
In the increasingly likely
event that you will die.

567
00:32:20.375 --> 00:32:23.333
would you like to notify
your next of kin on Uh-Earth?

568
00:32:23.416 --> 00:32:24.541
No. that's okay.

569
00:32:24.625 --> 00:32:26.875
Start from a position of power.

570
00:32:26.958 --> 00:32:30.541
The most important thing is to stay calm.

571
00:32:30.625 --> 00:32:32.458
Don't you tell me to stay calm!

572
00:32:32.541 --> 00:32:34.625
What is this. huh? A camp or a fight club?

573
00:32:34.708 --> 00:32:36.583
He's an innocent little boy.

574
00:32:36.666 --> 00:32:39.625
and if this is what you call
"building character."

575
00:32:39.708 --> 00:32:42.166
then I'll take it up
with your-- with your boss.

576
00:32:42.250 --> 00:32:43.750
or her-- her boss.

577
00:32:43.833 --> 00:32:45.000
Everyone's boss!

578
00:32:45.083 --> 00:32:46.375
Unacceptable!

579
00:32:50.458 --> 00:32:51.916
I never should have left you here.

580
00:32:52.000 --> 00:32:54.333
Yeah. they chased me
because I'm weak and small.

581
00:32:54.416 --> 00:32:55.916
but there was pizza for dinner.

582
00:32:56.000 --> 00:32:57.583
So. overall. a pretty good night.

583
00:32:57.666 --> 00:32:59.333
How's the eye? Swollen?

584
00:32:59.416 --> 00:33:00.541
-Did they hurt it?
-It's fine.

585
00:33:00.625 --> 00:33:02.458
I'm-I'm… I'm so sorry I didn't check in.

586
00:33:02.541 --> 00:33:04.750
Something weird was happening.

587
00:33:04.833 --> 00:33:06.250
That's okay.

588
00:33:06.333 --> 00:33:08.416
I was tracking this
crazy signal from space…

589
00:33:08.500 --> 00:33:10.166
Are we going home? What's for dinner?

590
00:33:10.250 --> 00:33:12.125
Um…

591
00:33:12.208 --> 00:33:13.458
Mac and cheese.

592
00:33:13.541 --> 00:33:15.000
I just thought you'd be interested

593
00:33:15.083 --> 00:33:18.416
because if aliens were calling from space…

594
00:33:18.500 --> 00:33:19.833
<i>Early morning fog and clouds</i>

595
00:33:19.916 --> 00:33:21.125
<i>along the coast…</i>

596
00:33:21.208 --> 00:33:22.125
Elio?

597
00:33:22.208 --> 00:33:24.791
Are we doing regular
or white cheddar? I'm starved.

598
00:33:24.875 --> 00:33:26.833
So. you-you-you don't want
to talk about aliens?

599
00:33:26.916 --> 00:33:29.583
Not really. I thought it'd be
better if I just dropped it.

600
00:33:29.666 --> 00:33:31.375
Really?

601
00:33:32.416 --> 00:33:34.500
That's… amazing.

602
00:33:35.458 --> 00:33:36.416
Good for you.

603
00:33:36.500 --> 00:33:37.625
Ooh!

604
00:33:39.000 --> 00:33:40.666
Oh. I love this song.

605
00:33:51.291 --> 00:33:52.291
Do you see him?

606
00:33:53.583 --> 00:33:55.375
Yes. and he's brought his…

607
00:33:56.208 --> 00:33:57.833
compatriots. Heh.

608
00:33:57.916 --> 00:33:58.916
Jolly good.

609
00:33:59.000 --> 00:34:02.416
Okay. Be confident. Speak
from a position of power.

610
00:34:02.500 --> 00:34:03.708
He's here!

611
00:34:03.791 --> 00:34:05.708
He's here. There he is.

612
00:34:05.791 --> 00:34:07.166
The man of the hour.

613
00:34:07.250 --> 00:34:08.541
Ah. Sorry I'm late.

614
00:34:08.625 --> 00:34:11.250
So. is Lord Grigon coming here?

615
00:34:11.333 --> 00:34:13.833
Oh. no. You will be going out there.

616
00:34:15.375 --> 00:34:16.958
Okay. bye. Love you.

617
00:34:19.333 --> 00:34:20.583
What is this?

618
00:34:21.125 --> 00:34:22.666
Red? Green?

619
00:34:22.750 --> 00:34:24.291
<i>Welcome. Captain Solís.</i>

620
00:34:24.375 --> 00:34:26.083
<i>You have selected</i>
<i>a map of our coordinates.</i>

621
00:34:26.166 --> 00:34:27.500
<i>Cabin pressure. Shield function.</i>

622
00:34:27.583 --> 00:34:29.375
<i>A nutritious shake. A breath mint.</i>

623
00:34:29.458 --> 00:34:30.583
<i>A bladder evacuation module.</i>

624
00:34:30.666 --> 00:34:32.500
Ah. he found the mint.

625
00:34:34.083 --> 00:34:36.458
<i>You have set our destination</i>
<i>to your home planet.</i>

626
00:34:36.541 --> 00:34:38.083
<i>Uh-Earth.</i>

627
00:34:38.166 --> 00:34:39.708
<i>Confirm or cancel?</i>

628
00:34:40.958 --> 00:34:42.208
Uh…

629
00:34:43.791 --> 00:34:45.125
Good luck.

630
00:34:48.833 --> 00:34:49.833
Cancel.

631
00:34:56.416 --> 00:34:58.250
Uh. okay. okay.

632
00:35:03.333 --> 00:35:04.291
A little to the left.

633
00:35:04.375 --> 00:35:06.500
Get your nubs at ten and two.

634
00:35:09.291 --> 00:35:11.083
Whoa!

635
00:35:11.166 --> 00:35:13.291
What a heroic figure he cuts.

636
00:35:43.041 --> 00:35:46.583
Hi. Take me to your leader?

637
00:35:52.916 --> 00:35:56.000
Okay. look him in the eye.
Stand your ground.

638
00:35:56.583 --> 00:35:58.291
You're the alpha. you're the killer.

639
00:35:58.375 --> 00:35:59.416
You're…

640
00:36:05.833 --> 00:36:08.375
This is who the Communiverse sends?

641
00:36:11.291 --> 00:36:14.125
You are more puny than I expected.

642
00:36:14.208 --> 00:36:16.166
I could say the same about you.

643
00:36:17.208 --> 00:36:18.958
-What?
-Uh…

644
00:36:19.041 --> 00:36:21.625
What do you need to leave
the Communiverse alone?

645
00:36:21.708 --> 00:36:25.750
Hylurgians prefer to negotiate
with screams in the air.

646
00:36:28.166 --> 00:36:29.250
Pull!

647
00:36:39.041 --> 00:36:41.166
Recoil's a little heavy.

648
00:36:43.083 --> 00:36:44.083
Your turn.

649
00:36:46.000 --> 00:36:49.625
Darn! I. uh. left my arm cannon at home.

650
00:36:49.708 --> 00:36:50.791
Why-Why don't we…

651
00:36:53.083 --> 00:36:54.625
Use one of mine.

652
00:36:54.708 --> 00:36:56.208
So nice of you.

653
00:36:56.291 --> 00:36:57.750
Uh…

654
00:36:59.916 --> 00:37:02.041
I-I mean. we're both leaders and. uh…

655
00:37:02.125 --> 00:37:03.458
Pull!

656
00:37:05.291 --> 00:37:08.416
Surely we could find something
to everyone's mutual…

657
00:37:10.750 --> 00:37:11.833
…benefit.

658
00:37:11.916 --> 00:37:13.625
Ah. trick shot.

659
00:37:13.708 --> 00:37:16.625
Perhaps we are able to communicate…

660
00:37:16.708 --> 00:37:17.541
Pull!

661
00:37:17.625 --> 00:37:20.208
But those Communiverse weaklings

662
00:37:20.291 --> 00:37:22.958
look at me like some kind of monster.

663
00:37:23.041 --> 00:37:24.625
How dare they reject me!

664
00:37:27.750 --> 00:37:29.500
Well. if they don't want you…

665
00:37:30.833 --> 00:37:32.916
…why not find someone who does?

666
00:37:33.500 --> 00:37:34.583
Come again?

667
00:37:34.666 --> 00:37:36.291
There's got to be a place out there

668
00:37:36.375 --> 00:37:40.208
that would love to have
a strong guy like you.

669
00:37:40.291 --> 00:37:41.708
But is the Communiverse not

670
00:37:41.791 --> 00:37:44.041
where the greatest leaders gather?

671
00:37:44.625 --> 00:37:46.000
Am I not great?

672
00:37:46.083 --> 00:37:47.166
T-Totally.

673
00:37:47.250 --> 00:37:49.041
But why waste your life

674
00:37:49.125 --> 00:37:51.250
trying to connect with people
who don't get you?

675
00:37:51.833 --> 00:37:53.291
It's time to move on.

676
00:37:53.375 --> 00:37:55.458
Right. Gri-guy?

677
00:37:56.083 --> 00:37:57.083
Gri-guy?

678
00:37:57.583 --> 00:37:59.208
Hmm. yes.

679
00:37:59.291 --> 00:38:01.000
What. Workko? What is it?

680
00:38:01.083 --> 00:38:03.458
Your Wrath. the princeling
wants to see you.

681
00:38:03.541 --> 00:38:06.958
For the hate of… Tell him I am busy!

682
00:38:07.041 --> 00:38:10.291
So. as we were saying.
forget the Communiverse…

683
00:38:10.375 --> 00:38:11.750
You are a father. right?

684
00:38:12.333 --> 00:38:14.083
Oh. Yeah.

685
00:38:14.166 --> 00:38:15.750
It is so difficult!

686
00:38:15.833 --> 00:38:19.583
He has no concept
of the importance of my work.

687
00:38:19.666 --> 00:38:20.666
I get it.

688
00:38:20.750 --> 00:38:23.625
If he's too hard to handle.
then just ship him off.

689
00:38:23.708 --> 00:38:25.416
That's what I did with mine. So…

690
00:38:25.500 --> 00:38:27.833
"Too hard to handle"?

691
00:38:31.583 --> 00:38:32.625
I-I mean…

692
00:38:32.708 --> 00:38:35.041
Oh. you think I cannot handle my own son?

693
00:38:35.125 --> 00:38:36.750
No. no. no. I-I don't think that…

694
00:38:36.833 --> 00:38:39.333
No! Really. Tell me what I am doing wrong!

695
00:38:39.416 --> 00:38:42.083
It's okay. I'm a bad parent too.

696
00:38:42.166 --> 00:38:43.500
What?

697
00:38:43.583 --> 00:38:44.833
None of us know what we're doing.

698
00:38:44.916 --> 00:38:46.916
We-We didn't even want this. right?

699
00:38:47.000 --> 00:38:49.500
Let me remind you
who you are dealing with!

700
00:38:49.583 --> 00:38:53.625
I am Grigon. Blood Emperor of Hylurg.

701
00:38:53.708 --> 00:38:58.416
scourge of the Crab Nebula
and a great father!

702
00:38:58.500 --> 00:38:59.708
Pull!

703
00:39:04.333 --> 00:39:06.875
Right. why don't
we take a little breather…

704
00:39:06.958 --> 00:39:09.208
The negotiation is over.

705
00:39:09.291 --> 00:39:10.125
Gronk!

706
00:39:10.208 --> 00:39:12.500
Show the prisoner to his quarters!

707
00:39:12.583 --> 00:39:13.875
Prisoner? What?

708
00:39:13.958 --> 00:39:15.750
You will watch from a cell

709
00:39:15.833 --> 00:39:18.791
as I destroy your beloved Communiverse!

710
00:39:18.875 --> 00:39:20.291
No. no. wait!

711
00:39:23.583 --> 00:39:25.416
He's really turned over a new leaf.

712
00:39:26.375 --> 00:39:28.791
-Hey. Elio.
-Hey. Jim. How's your back?

713
00:39:28.875 --> 00:39:30.666
-Oh. you know…
-I hear ya.

714
00:39:30.750 --> 00:39:32.958
Oh. camp must've really helped.

715
00:39:33.041 --> 00:39:34.416
I guess it did.

716
00:39:34.500 --> 00:39:37.375
But he was only there for one day.

717
00:39:37.458 --> 00:39:39.875
Oh. I overheard
the colonel raving about you.

718
00:39:39.958 --> 00:39:41.708
Really? She was?

719
00:39:41.791 --> 00:39:42.791
Yeah.

720
00:39:42.875 --> 00:39:44.291
You've been working really hard.

721
00:39:44.375 --> 00:39:46.208
Oh. that's so good to hear.

722
00:39:46.291 --> 00:39:48.541
I thought I'd never get off her bad side.

723
00:39:48.625 --> 00:39:49.500
Oopsie.

724
00:39:49.583 --> 00:39:51.333
Everyone's super impressed.

725
00:39:56.000 --> 00:39:58.208
Wait. please. You made a mistake.

726
00:39:58.291 --> 00:40:00.041
I'm the leader of Earth!

727
00:40:34.500 --> 00:40:37.791
Uh. gravity. um… off.

728
00:40:38.458 --> 00:40:39.541
Whoa.

729
00:40:48.416 --> 00:40:50.458
Okay. th-that's enough! Gravity back!

730
00:40:53.500 --> 00:40:55.791
Okay. I'll just get back to Grigon.

731
00:40:55.875 --> 00:40:57.166
Uh. what haven't I tried?

732
00:40:58.083 --> 00:41:01.333
"Bargaining chip"?
Like. something valuable?

733
00:41:01.416 --> 00:41:02.708
Where am I going to find…

734
00:41:26.250 --> 00:41:27.541
H-Hi. there.

735
00:41:35.541 --> 00:41:38.083
I'm too young to die.
I'm too young to die.

736
00:41:38.166 --> 00:41:39.916
I'm too young to die.

737
00:41:45.125 --> 00:41:47.750
- What's happening?
- What's happening?

738
00:41:47.833 --> 00:41:50.500
Whoa. Translator disc. cool.

739
00:41:50.583 --> 00:41:52.000
-Are you going to eat me?
-What?

740
00:41:52.083 --> 00:41:55.625
Ew. I was just swaddling you
because you seemed scared.

741
00:41:55.708 --> 00:41:57.791
That's what my mom does when I get scared.

742
00:41:57.875 --> 00:42:00.375
I'm rarely unswaddled.

743
00:42:00.458 --> 00:42:01.958
You're just a little kid.

744
00:42:02.583 --> 00:42:05.250
So? Don't have to be rude about it.

745
00:42:06.625 --> 00:42:08.875
Oh. No. no. no. Hey. come back!

746
00:42:08.958 --> 00:42:10.291
I wasn't making fun of you!

747
00:42:11.291 --> 00:42:13.583
Uh. my name's Elio.

748
00:42:13.666 --> 00:42:15.333
W-What's your name?

749
00:42:15.416 --> 00:42:17.500
You really want to know my name?

750
00:42:17.583 --> 00:42:20.583
Well. I really want to get down.

751
00:42:20.666 --> 00:42:23.833
I'm Glordon! No one's ever
asked me my name before.

752
00:42:24.833 --> 00:42:26.500
I mean. I ask a lot
of questions all the time.

753
00:42:26.583 --> 00:42:28.958
No one ever asks me about
questions about me. though.

754
00:42:29.041 --> 00:42:30.583
Like what my favorite color is.

755
00:42:30.666 --> 00:42:32.541
It's purple. if you're asking.
Are you asking?

756
00:42:39.458 --> 00:42:42.041
What's wrong with you?
That's just my carapace.

757
00:42:42.125 --> 00:42:44.041
-W-What?
-I'll show you.

758
00:42:52.041 --> 00:42:53.583
Ta-da!

759
00:42:53.666 --> 00:42:54.666
Whoa.

760
00:42:55.291 --> 00:42:57.875
Every Hylurgian gets one
when they come of age.

761
00:42:57.958 --> 00:43:00.333
It's got weapons and bombs and stuff.

762
00:43:00.416 --> 00:43:01.958
Ooh. and a cup holder!

763
00:43:02.041 --> 00:43:03.583
It's bespoke.

764
00:43:03.666 --> 00:43:06.625
So. if Hylurgians took off their armor.

765
00:43:06.708 --> 00:43:07.708
they'd look like you?

766
00:43:07.791 --> 00:43:09.916
Yeah. but nobody would ever do that.

767
00:43:10.000 --> 00:43:12.208
To expose your soft. warm flesh

768
00:43:12.291 --> 00:43:14.291
would dishonor you and your whole family

769
00:43:14.375 --> 00:43:15.791
for all eternity.

770
00:43:15.875 --> 00:43:17.208
I can't wait to get installed.

771
00:43:17.791 --> 00:43:19.250
I'm going to look so hot.

772
00:43:20.250 --> 00:43:22.083
<i>Alert! A prisoner has escaped.</i>

773
00:43:22.166 --> 00:43:23.708
-Oh. no.
-Are they talking about you?

774
00:43:23.791 --> 00:43:26.125
Uh. it's a complicated
political situation.

775
00:43:26.208 --> 00:43:27.375
You-You wouldn't understand.

776
00:43:27.458 --> 00:43:28.583
Are you a treacherous dissident?

777
00:43:28.666 --> 00:43:30.083
Where is he?
Check every chamber!

778
00:43:30.166 --> 00:43:31.000
Are you an assassin?

779
00:43:31.083 --> 00:43:32.250
You two with me. Move!

780
00:43:32.333 --> 00:43:34.125
-What'd you do?
-Uh. uh…

781
00:43:34.208 --> 00:43:36.416
Come on. I'm really good
at keeping secrets.

782
00:43:37.000 --> 00:43:39.083
- Nothing here. sir.
- Keep looking!

783
00:43:39.583 --> 00:43:40.875
The secret is…

784
00:43:41.458 --> 00:43:42.541
I'm a kid.

785
00:43:42.625 --> 00:43:43.958
What? Really?

786
00:43:44.541 --> 00:43:45.416
Mm-hmm.

787
00:43:45.500 --> 00:43:47.958
And I kind of
tricked the Communiverse…

788
00:43:48.041 --> 00:43:49.500
Whoa.

789
00:43:49.583 --> 00:43:50.416
What?

790
00:43:50.500 --> 00:43:53.333
Oh.

791
00:43:53.416 --> 00:43:54.500
No way!

792
00:43:54.583 --> 00:43:56.041
You're crazy.

793
00:43:56.125 --> 00:43:59.166
I know and now Grigon's
going to blow everyone up

794
00:43:59.250 --> 00:44:01.375
unless I can find a bargaining chip.

795
00:44:01.458 --> 00:44:05.166
Something he values. but what
does he even value?

796
00:44:05.250 --> 00:44:08.791
Well. Dad values blood. glory.
the misery of his enemies.

797
00:44:08.875 --> 00:44:10.041
Ooh. There was this one time…

798
00:44:10.125 --> 00:44:12.750
Hold up. Grigon's your dad?

799
00:44:12.833 --> 00:44:15.083
I thought you knew. I look just like him.

800
00:44:15.166 --> 00:44:17.708
Check it out.

801
00:44:22.208 --> 00:44:23.583
I've been working on my back.

802
00:44:26.791 --> 00:44:30.458
Can I ask you a big favor?

803
00:44:31.500 --> 00:44:32.750
Sure.

804
00:44:32.833 --> 00:44:34.666
Bargaining chip. Cool.

805
00:44:34.750 --> 00:44:36.458
I've never been a bargaining chip before.

806
00:44:36.541 --> 00:44:38.791
I've been a liability. A disappointment.

807
00:44:38.875 --> 00:44:41.166
-A deduction.
-Are we almost to my ship?

808
00:44:41.250 --> 00:44:44.375
Not far now. I've also been
a pillow. an enigma.

809
00:44:44.458 --> 00:44:46.208
a problem. a headache.

810
00:44:47.416 --> 00:44:49.666
Little help. please.

811
00:44:49.750 --> 00:44:51.166
Lately. I've just been ignored.

812
00:44:51.250 --> 00:44:53.875
but now my dad's finally
going to pay attention to me.

813
00:44:53.958 --> 00:44:55.875
Do your parents pay attention to you?

814
00:44:55.958 --> 00:44:57.958
Well. my Aunt Olga doesn't care.

815
00:44:58.041 --> 00:44:59.375
With me out the way

816
00:44:59.458 --> 00:45:01.500
she can do what she really wants.

817
00:45:02.458 --> 00:45:04.333
Like be an astronaut or whatever.

818
00:45:04.416 --> 00:45:07.500
She gave up being an astronaut
or whatever for you?

819
00:45:07.583 --> 00:45:09.250
Wow. She must really love you.

820
00:45:10.375 --> 00:45:12.291
No. no. she doesn't.

821
00:45:12.375 --> 00:45:15.166
But now I'm free to join the Communiverse.

822
00:45:15.250 --> 00:45:17.083
which is where I belong anyway

823
00:45:17.166 --> 00:45:18.833
and that's where you come in.

824
00:45:18.916 --> 00:45:20.250
bargaining chip.

825
00:45:20.333 --> 00:45:21.416
Whee!

826
00:45:23.166 --> 00:45:25.041
- Ow.
- Oof!

827
00:45:25.125 --> 00:45:27.125
Wiggle.

828
00:45:27.208 --> 00:45:28.625
Wiggle.

829
00:45:28.708 --> 00:45:31.333
<i>Candidate Solís?</i>
<i>Sorry to bother you.</i>

830
00:45:31.416 --> 00:45:33.916
It's just that the Hylurgian ships

831
00:45:34.000 --> 00:45:36.291
seem to be pointing their cannons at us.

832
00:45:36.375 --> 00:45:38.375
<i>Is this part of the negotiations?</i>

833
00:45:38.458 --> 00:45:40.916
Oh. that's just a drill. Don't worry.

834
00:45:41.000 --> 00:45:43.083
Wiggle.

835
00:45:45.375 --> 00:45:47.833
- Whoa.
- Come on.

836
00:45:47.916 --> 00:45:49.333
What are these tunnels for. anyway?

837
00:45:49.416 --> 00:45:52.541
Oh. these are the lava flumes.
They power the cannons.

838
00:45:54.458 --> 00:45:56.375
Glordon. I am not fireproof!

839
00:45:56.458 --> 00:45:57.833
Really? Why didn't you say something?

840
00:45:57.916 --> 00:45:58.958
Glordon!

841
00:45:59.041 --> 00:46:01.625
It's okay. Just get in my mouth.

842
00:46:02.541 --> 00:46:03.916
What? No way!

843
00:46:04.000 --> 00:46:05.083
Trust me.

844
00:46:13.041 --> 00:46:14.041
Hmm.

845
00:46:14.125 --> 00:46:16.333
It's. uh. actually kind of comfy in here.

846
00:46:16.416 --> 00:46:18.083
It is? I've never been in there.

847
00:46:18.166 --> 00:46:19.166
Hold on.

848
00:46:24.208 --> 00:46:25.541
Yeah!

849
00:46:28.791 --> 00:46:30.583
Ah. Refreshing.

850
00:46:32.500 --> 00:46:33.500
You okay?

851
00:46:34.916 --> 00:46:35.916
Yes!

852
00:46:36.000 --> 00:46:37.458
Lower me down.

853
00:46:41.166 --> 00:46:42.750
Thanks. Glordon.

854
00:46:42.833 --> 00:46:44.958
Eh. It's nothing. Up top.

855
00:46:47.458 --> 00:46:50.083
How long's the flight?
Any snacks on board?

856
00:46:53.750 --> 00:46:55.750
Ah. it's Candidate Solís!

857
00:46:55.833 --> 00:46:58.000
I'm sure he's bringing good news.

858
00:46:58.083 --> 00:46:58.916
Oh.

859
00:46:59.000 --> 00:47:00.000
Look out!

860
00:47:06.500 --> 00:47:08.125
I'm so excited. I'm so excited.

861
00:47:08.208 --> 00:47:09.125
I'm so excited.

862
00:47:09.208 --> 00:47:10.875
-Candidate Solís?
-What's happened?

863
00:47:10.958 --> 00:47:12.958
Ooooo. open a line to Lord Grigon!

864
00:47:13.041 --> 00:47:15.083
-Of course.
-Who is this?

865
00:47:15.166 --> 00:47:16.625
<i>Who is responsible for…</i>

866
00:47:17.583 --> 00:47:18.541
- <i>You!</i>
- Yes.

867
00:47:18.625 --> 00:47:21.041
It's me! The leader of Earth.

868
00:47:21.125 --> 00:47:23.041
And the negotiation is not over

869
00:47:23.125 --> 00:47:25.083
because now I've got this!

870
00:47:25.166 --> 00:47:26.000
Oh. my.

871
00:47:26.083 --> 00:47:27.333
<i>Glordon?</i>

872
00:47:27.416 --> 00:47:31.833
Yes. and-and pretty soon
he's going to be Glor-done.

873
00:47:31.916 --> 00:47:33.833
Hi. Dad. I'm a bargaining chip.

874
00:47:33.916 --> 00:47:35.125
No. Say the other thing.

875
00:47:35.208 --> 00:47:37.916
Oh. Help me. Father. He overpowered me.

876
00:47:38.000 --> 00:47:41.000
He's too strong. Too shredded.

877
00:47:41.083 --> 00:47:42.333
Quiet. you!

878
00:47:43.750 --> 00:47:46.875
<i>What is that unholy sound? Stop! Stop!</i>

879
00:47:46.958 --> 00:47:48.166
Only if you swear…

880
00:47:48.250 --> 00:47:49.875
On your Hylurgian honor.

881
00:47:49.958 --> 00:47:51.916
Oh. On your Hylurgian honor

882
00:47:52.000 --> 00:47:55.041
to leave the Communiverse
in peace and never return.

883
00:47:55.125 --> 00:47:57.250
<i>My Hylurgian honor?</i>

884
00:47:57.333 --> 00:47:59.250
<i>Do you know what you are asking?</i>

885
00:47:59.333 --> 00:48:00.500
<i>I will…</i>

886
00:48:04.458 --> 00:48:06.208
<i>Stop!</i>

887
00:48:06.291 --> 00:48:08.083
<i>I-I concede!</i>

888
00:48:10.125 --> 00:48:13.083
<i>I swear on my honor…</i>

889
00:48:14.416 --> 00:48:16.708
<i>You are full of surprises.</i>

890
00:48:16.791 --> 00:48:17.958
<i>You have my vow.</i>

891
00:48:19.208 --> 00:48:21.708
<i>I will come to collect my son.</i>

892
00:48:21.791 --> 00:48:25.416
<i>but if even one hair</i>
<i>on a single nub is harmed.</i>

893
00:48:25.500 --> 00:48:28.083
<i>you will feel my wrath.</i>

894
00:48:30.333 --> 00:48:32.875
Well done. I knew you had it in you.

895
00:48:32.958 --> 00:48:34.375
Thank you.

896
00:48:34.458 --> 00:48:36.458
Oh. I can't wait for this all to be over.

897
00:48:36.541 --> 00:48:39.166
and officially welcome you into the fold.

898
00:48:39.250 --> 00:48:42.041
I'm customizing your
membership badge right now.

899
00:48:42.125 --> 00:48:43.250
Do you like the color?

900
00:48:44.250 --> 00:48:45.333
It's beautiful.

901
00:48:45.416 --> 00:48:47.250
And so well-deserved.

902
00:48:47.333 --> 00:48:50.208
But first. let's prepare
for Lord Grigon's arrival.

903
00:48:50.291 --> 00:48:51.666
Come. everyone. Chop-chop.

904
00:48:54.291 --> 00:48:56.000
Uh. you guys go ahead.

905
00:48:56.083 --> 00:48:58.666
I'll take care of the bargaining chip.

906
00:48:58.750 --> 00:49:00.166
Very good. Candidate Solís.

907
00:49:00.250 --> 00:49:02.416
Now. does anyone know a good caterer?

908
00:49:04.750 --> 00:49:06.416
Oh. we did it.

909
00:49:06.500 --> 00:49:09.541
Yeah. You were so cool.

910
00:49:09.625 --> 00:49:11.166
Oh. you okay?

911
00:49:11.250 --> 00:49:13.958
I've never been outside before.

912
00:49:14.041 --> 00:49:15.666
It's cold here.

913
00:49:18.250 --> 00:49:21.083
Wow! This thing's amazing.

914
00:49:21.166 --> 00:49:22.166
Watch this.

915
00:49:22.250 --> 00:49:23.375
Gravity off.

916
00:49:26.791 --> 00:49:27.791
Whoa.

917
00:49:27.875 --> 00:49:29.458
Gravity off.

918
00:49:31.250 --> 00:49:33.250
Whoo-hoo!

919
00:49:34.208 --> 00:49:36.541
You think this is cool? Come on!

920
00:49:38.500 --> 00:49:40.375
Your Wrath. the shuttle is ready.

921
00:49:40.458 --> 00:49:41.708
Shall we depart?

922
00:49:41.791 --> 00:49:43.458
No. not yet.

923
00:49:43.958 --> 00:49:47.500
The princeling was taken
because he was vulnerable…

924
00:49:47.583 --> 00:49:50.416
exposed. soft.

925
00:49:51.041 --> 00:49:52.875
Prepare his carapace.

926
00:49:52.958 --> 00:49:55.041
But that will take time. Your Bloodness…

927
00:49:55.125 --> 00:49:56.125
Do it!

928
00:49:56.208 --> 00:49:59.250
We will perform Glordon's
ceremony on the Communiverse

929
00:49:59.833 --> 00:50:03.875
and they will quiver
at the full might of Hylurg!

930
00:50:06.375 --> 00:50:08.166
- Ready?
- Yes.

931
00:50:08.250 --> 00:50:09.583
No.

932
00:50:09.666 --> 00:50:10.958
O-Okay. yes!

933
00:50:11.041 --> 00:50:12.125
On three.

934
00:50:12.208 --> 00:50:14.041
One. two…

935
00:50:14.125 --> 00:50:15.833
-Two and a half.
-Two and a half.

936
00:50:16.416 --> 00:50:17.333
Three!

937
00:50:24.250 --> 00:50:25.750
-Again?
-Heck. yeah. again.

938
00:50:25.833 --> 00:50:26.791
On three.

939
00:50:26.875 --> 00:50:27.875
One. two.

940
00:50:28.708 --> 00:50:30.083
Whoo-hoo!

941
00:50:34.083 --> 00:50:35.083
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

942
00:50:37.958 --> 00:50:40.000
-Whoo!
-Yeah!

943
00:51:03.750 --> 00:51:04.750
Whoo!

944
00:51:16.500 --> 00:51:17.833
Ha-ha!

945
00:51:27.916 --> 00:51:30.583
<i>Shmeepa skiddopoo-peh.</i>

946
00:51:30.666 --> 00:51:31.666
No. no.

947
00:51:31.750 --> 00:51:33.291
<i>Skiddopop-puh.</i>

948
00:51:33.375 --> 00:51:34.291
Noice.

949
00:51:34.375 --> 00:51:36.750
<i>Shmeepa skiddopop-popopop-puh!</i>

950
00:51:38.583 --> 00:51:40.958
So. everyone speaks Elioese on Earth?

951
00:51:41.041 --> 00:51:42.375
Nah. just me.

952
00:51:42.916 --> 00:51:44.291
And my parents.

953
00:51:45.416 --> 00:51:47.916
Or at least they did.

954
00:51:48.000 --> 00:51:49.666
My aunt's not into it.

955
00:51:50.333 --> 00:51:53.875
but I keep using it so I don't forget.

956
00:51:55.083 --> 00:51:58.000
Did something happen to your parents?

957
00:51:59.583 --> 00:52:00.583
Yeah.

958
00:52:02.125 --> 00:52:03.125
I'm sorry.

959
00:52:03.875 --> 00:52:07.333
I know it's not the same.
but my mom's gone a lot.

960
00:52:07.416 --> 00:52:09.083
Fighting the Blood Wars.

961
00:52:09.875 --> 00:52:11.041
I miss her a ton.

962
00:52:11.916 --> 00:52:15.125
Sometimes it feels like
Dad doesn't even want me.

963
00:52:16.916 --> 00:52:18.000
I know what you mean.

964
00:52:20.916 --> 00:52:24.125
The only people who wanted me are gone.

965
00:52:24.916 --> 00:52:27.083
But I don't know.

966
00:52:29.083 --> 00:52:30.083
What if…

967
00:52:31.708 --> 00:52:34.375
What if there's nothing about me to want?

968
00:52:36.375 --> 00:52:38.666
I thought Earth was the problem.

969
00:52:38.750 --> 00:52:39.833
but…

970
00:52:41.166 --> 00:52:42.583
what if it's me?

971
00:52:44.375 --> 00:52:46.166
Well. I like you.

972
00:52:47.208 --> 00:52:48.500
And you seem fine to me.

973
00:53:18.208 --> 00:53:21.000
Oh. He brought your carapace.

974
00:53:21.083 --> 00:53:22.375
I guess so?

975
00:53:22.458 --> 00:53:24.333
But that's good. right?

976
00:53:24.416 --> 00:53:26.500
Yeah. I mean. it has a flame thrower.

977
00:53:26.583 --> 00:53:28.458
a circular saw. acid gun.

978
00:53:28.541 --> 00:53:32.416
I'll get to fight.
and conquer. and kill. and…

979
00:53:34.791 --> 00:53:35.791
Glordon.

980
00:53:36.291 --> 00:53:38.500
do you not want to get into your carapace?

981
00:53:38.583 --> 00:53:41.166
Yeah. I mean. kind of. well…

982
00:53:41.250 --> 00:53:42.875
No. no.

983
00:53:42.958 --> 00:53:44.416
I've been pretending to want it.

984
00:53:44.500 --> 00:53:46.333
but I've been living a lie!

985
00:53:49.833 --> 00:53:53.250
Once I'm installed. I'll never
get to play. or swim.

986
00:53:53.333 --> 00:53:54.875
or do anything.

987
00:53:54.958 --> 00:53:56.291
It'll be the worst!

988
00:53:58.500 --> 00:54:00.375
But why didn't you say something?

989
00:54:00.458 --> 00:54:02.833
Because all Hylurgians have to do it!

990
00:54:02.916 --> 00:54:04.166
It's tradition.

991
00:54:04.250 --> 00:54:05.791
And if I don't…

992
00:54:07.375 --> 00:54:09.375
…my dad would hate me.

993
00:54:16.500 --> 00:54:18.833
Glordon. you're not getting in there.

994
00:54:18.916 --> 00:54:21.625
But… I don't have a choice.

995
00:54:22.208 --> 00:54:23.333
We'll figure it out.

996
00:54:24.041 --> 00:54:25.541
I don't know how. but…

997
00:54:28.125 --> 00:54:29.125
Oh. wait.

998
00:54:29.208 --> 00:54:30.458
Ha!

999
00:54:30.541 --> 00:54:31.541
What?

1000
00:54:32.833 --> 00:54:34.750
Ooh. What are we doing?

1001
00:54:34.833 --> 00:54:36.250
We're going to give your dad
what he wants.

1002
00:54:36.333 --> 00:54:37.333
Me?

1003
00:54:37.416 --> 00:54:38.750
Well. yes. but also no.

1004
00:54:39.833 --> 00:54:41.750
Cloning clay? A-Are you sure about this?

1005
00:54:41.833 --> 00:54:43.250
Yeah. Why not?

1006
00:54:43.333 --> 00:54:44.625
I don't know.

1007
00:54:44.708 --> 00:54:46.375
Would a clone really fool my dad?

1008
00:54:46.458 --> 00:54:47.666
He's pretty smart.

1009
00:54:47.750 --> 00:54:50.041
Oh. it's going to work. I'll show you.

1010
00:54:50.125 --> 00:54:51.416
Ooooo? Ooooo?

1011
00:54:51.500 --> 00:54:53.833
-Yes?
-Can I check on my clone?

1012
00:54:53.916 --> 00:54:54.916
Certainly.

1013
00:54:55.000 --> 00:54:57.375
Mmm. That smells good. <i>papito</i>.

1014
00:54:57.458 --> 00:54:58.541
It's a secret recipe.

1015
00:54:58.625 --> 00:54:59.958
You're going to love it.

1016
00:55:00.041 --> 00:55:01.958
How are you so good at everything?

1017
00:55:06.208 --> 00:55:08.166
Mmm. mmm. mmm.

1018
00:55:08.250 --> 00:55:10.333
Wow. I guess it does work.

1019
00:55:10.416 --> 00:55:12.041
Okay. let's do it.

1020
00:55:12.541 --> 00:55:13.541
Yeah.

1021
00:55:14.375 --> 00:55:15.458
Yeah!

1022
00:55:15.541 --> 00:55:18.291
<i>Okay. Your dad will take</i>
<i>your clone back to Hylurg.</i>

1023
00:55:18.375 --> 00:55:19.875
<i>I'll become an Ambassador.</i>

1024
00:55:19.958 --> 00:55:21.791
<i>and neither of us will have to see Hylurg.</i>

1025
00:55:21.875 --> 00:55:23.041
<i>or stupid Earth again.</i>

1026
00:55:23.125 --> 00:55:24.583
<i>It's a win-win-win.</i>

1027
00:55:29.583 --> 00:55:31.000
-Whoa.
-Yes.

1028
00:55:35.083 --> 00:55:36.083
I'm Glordon!

1029
00:55:36.166 --> 00:55:38.250
Wow! Am I really that ripped?

1030
00:55:38.333 --> 00:55:39.416
You. follow us.

1031
00:55:39.500 --> 00:55:40.583
You got it.

1032
00:55:44.708 --> 00:55:46.708
You'll be safe in here.
No one else can open it.

1033
00:55:48.083 --> 00:55:49.750
All right. Glordon. get in the ship.

1034
00:55:49.833 --> 00:55:50.791
Okay.

1035
00:55:50.875 --> 00:55:51.916
I can't tell you apart.

1036
00:55:52.000 --> 00:55:53.458
- Yes!
- Whoo-hoo!

1037
00:55:53.541 --> 00:55:55.125
Seriously. though. which one's real?

1038
00:55:55.208 --> 00:55:56.208
Me.

1039
00:55:58.125 --> 00:56:00.375
Stay inside and don't make a sound.

1040
00:56:02.916 --> 00:56:04.000
I'll be right back.

1041
00:56:08.375 --> 00:56:09.375
Come on.

1042
00:56:11.458 --> 00:56:14.333
You look so good. I can't
even tell the difference.

1043
00:56:14.416 --> 00:56:15.458
Mmm.

1044
00:56:15.541 --> 00:56:17.291
I can't even tell the difference.

1045
00:56:17.375 --> 00:56:18.458
I know.

1046
00:56:18.541 --> 00:56:21.041
Who knew yogurt is just
as yummy as butter…

1047
00:56:21.125 --> 00:56:23.125
…and half the cholesterol?

1048
00:56:24.500 --> 00:56:25.750
It's perfect.

1049
00:56:27.458 --> 00:56:28.500
Let me get that for you.

1050
00:56:28.583 --> 00:56:30.583
Aw. Thanks so much.

1051
00:56:34.208 --> 00:56:36.875
Well. I'm going to
turn in for the night.

1052
00:56:36.958 --> 00:56:40.583
All right. But first.
get over here. kiddo.

1053
00:56:40.666 --> 00:56:41.833
Mwah.

1054
00:56:44.166 --> 00:56:45.333
Good night.

1055
00:57:12.291 --> 00:57:13.291
Hmm.

1056
00:57:23.250 --> 00:57:24.250
What the?

1057
00:58:19.083 --> 00:58:20.750
Hi. We should probably talk.

1058
00:58:24.750 --> 00:58:26.416
And for my next trick.

1059
00:58:26.500 --> 00:58:27.791
think of a number.

1060
00:58:27.875 --> 00:58:30.500
Uh. wait. Uh…

1061
00:58:30.583 --> 00:58:31.708
Okay. got it!

1062
00:58:32.250 --> 00:58:33.458
Yes. Yes. yes. yes.

1063
00:58:33.541 --> 00:58:35.750
I don't know
how much longer we can stall.

1064
00:58:35.833 --> 00:58:36.916
Where is Candidate Solís?

1065
00:58:37.000 --> 00:58:39.375
I'm sure he'll be here momentarily.

1066
00:58:39.458 --> 00:58:42.208
I sense the number is

1067
00:58:42.291 --> 00:58:44.125
-seven.
-What?

1068
00:58:44.208 --> 00:58:46.000
- Aw. she's right.
- Enough!

1069
00:58:46.583 --> 00:58:48.375
Where is my son?

1070
00:58:49.208 --> 00:58:51.208
He's here. He's right here.

1071
00:58:51.291 --> 00:58:52.291
Daddy.

1072
00:58:53.041 --> 00:58:55.125
-He did not abandon us.
-He's here!

1073
00:58:55.208 --> 00:58:56.750
Thank the stars.

1074
00:58:56.833 --> 00:59:00.375
Lord Grigon. we return
to you Prince Glordon.

1075
00:59:00.458 --> 00:59:02.541
My son. Did he harm you?

1076
00:59:02.625 --> 00:59:04.708
Nope. Everyone was super nice.

1077
00:59:04.791 --> 00:59:07.333
Hmm. Are you prepared to become

1078
00:59:07.416 --> 00:59:10.291
the greatest war machine in the universe?

1079
00:59:10.375 --> 00:59:13.750
To make your enemies tremble
at the sight of you?

1080
00:59:13.833 --> 00:59:15.458
To prove the might of the…

1081
00:59:15.541 --> 00:59:16.625
Yep! Let's do it!

1082
00:59:17.625 --> 00:59:18.916
Oh.

1083
00:59:19.000 --> 00:59:21.041
A-Actually. I had more to say.

1084
00:59:21.125 --> 00:59:23.708
but. yes. l-l-let us get on with it.

1085
01:00:33.708 --> 01:00:34.750
Whoo!

1086
01:00:35.250 --> 01:00:36.250
Oh. yeah.

1087
01:00:38.625 --> 01:00:40.250
- Whew.
- Whew.

1088
01:00:42.791 --> 01:00:45.375
Witness the power of Hylurg.

1089
01:00:46.250 --> 01:00:47.333
Witness!

1090
01:00:47.416 --> 01:00:49.166
-What a good show.
-Very impressive.

1091
01:00:49.250 --> 01:00:50.916
That's right.

1092
01:00:52.125 --> 01:00:53.708
As you have kept your word.

1093
01:00:53.791 --> 01:00:57.750
I will keep mine and leave
this place. never to return.

1094
01:00:57.833 --> 01:01:00.083
Hylurgians. fall back.

1095
01:01:01.083 --> 01:01:02.625
Candidate Solís. you did it!

1096
01:01:02.708 --> 01:01:04.875
Well done.

1097
01:01:04.958 --> 01:01:06.375
What an exceptional specimen.

1098
01:01:06.458 --> 01:01:07.791
You good. Son?

1099
01:01:07.875 --> 01:01:10.833
Oh. yeah. I can't wait to make endless war

1100
01:01:10.916 --> 01:01:13.125
and pillage the unworthy
and bring eternal night…

1101
01:01:13.208 --> 01:01:16.708
May I have the honor
of joining the Communiverse?

1102
01:01:17.416 --> 01:01:20.791
The honor would be ours. Candidate Solís.

1103
01:01:20.875 --> 01:01:23.875
Or should I say. Ambassador Solís.

1104
01:01:23.958 --> 01:01:25.458
-You're one of us now.
-You're amazing!

1105
01:01:25.541 --> 01:01:26.541
- I like you.
- Welcome!

1106
01:01:37.750 --> 01:01:39.083
Ah.

1107
01:01:39.166 --> 01:01:40.291
It was a clone.

1108
01:01:40.375 --> 01:01:42.333
Where is my son?

1109
01:01:42.416 --> 01:01:44.083
But…

1110
01:01:44.666 --> 01:01:45.625
How could you tell?

1111
01:01:45.708 --> 01:01:48.750
A father always knows.

1112
01:01:50.583 --> 01:01:52.750
You. read his mind.

1113
01:01:52.833 --> 01:01:54.333
Find the truth.

1114
01:01:54.416 --> 01:01:55.416
No.

1115
01:01:56.208 --> 01:01:57.291
Unhand me!

1116
01:01:57.375 --> 01:01:58.458
I'm so sorry.

1117
01:01:58.541 --> 01:01:59.833
No.

1118
01:01:59.916 --> 01:02:00.916
No.

1119
01:02:02.666 --> 01:02:05.166
No. no. No. no. please. No!

1120
01:02:09.208 --> 01:02:11.208
What? What did you see?

1121
01:02:11.291 --> 01:02:15.500
Your son is in a diplomatic
ship in the docking bay.

1122
01:02:15.583 --> 01:02:17.041
Send the troops!

1123
01:02:22.333 --> 01:02:23.875
Oh. more pudding. Elio?

1124
01:02:23.958 --> 01:02:25.375
Why. thank you. Glordon!

1125
01:02:34.500 --> 01:02:35.541
Elio?

1126
01:02:38.916 --> 01:02:40.875
<i> You have selected</i>
<i>a map of our coordinates.</i>

1127
01:02:40.958 --> 01:02:42.916
<i>Neck pillow. Lip balm. A breath mint.</i>

1128
01:02:43.000 --> 01:02:43.833
Mmm.

1129
01:02:43.916 --> 01:02:45.000
<i>Destination…</i>

1130
01:02:45.083 --> 01:02:46.208
<i>Uh. Earth.</i>

1131
01:02:46.291 --> 01:02:48.083
<i>Confirm or cancel?</i>

1132
01:02:48.166 --> 01:02:50.250
What? Confirm?

1133
01:02:58.208 --> 01:03:01.250
Ooooo. open a portal to Earth.

1134
01:03:03.291 --> 01:03:04.625
What are you doing?

1135
01:03:04.708 --> 01:03:07.125
Will you tell them. or must I?

1136
01:03:08.750 --> 01:03:09.750
Please don't.

1137
01:03:10.333 --> 01:03:12.083
He is not the leader of Earth.

1138
01:03:13.250 --> 01:03:15.291
He is not the leader of anything.

1139
01:03:15.791 --> 01:03:17.208
He is just

1140
01:03:17.291 --> 01:03:18.291
a child.

1141
01:03:18.875 --> 01:03:19.833
-What?
-Oh. no.

1142
01:03:19.916 --> 01:03:20.916
-I do not understand.
-No.

1143
01:03:21.000 --> 01:03:22.791
She's… She's wrong.

1144
01:03:23.416 --> 01:03:26.041
I am the leader of Earth.

1145
01:03:27.833 --> 01:03:29.291
I can still help!

1146
01:03:29.375 --> 01:03:31.750
Just please. please let me stay.

1147
01:03:32.416 --> 01:03:33.750
He is not there!

1148
01:03:33.833 --> 01:03:35.250
-What?
-But I saw him!

1149
01:03:35.333 --> 01:03:36.708
We are as surprised as you.

1150
01:03:36.791 --> 01:03:37.958
Arrest them all!

1151
01:03:38.041 --> 01:03:42.083
The Communiverse is now
under Hylurgian control.

1152
01:03:51.166 --> 01:03:53.041
Don't touch me. Stop!

1153
01:03:53.125 --> 01:03:54.125
We can sort this out!

1154
01:03:54.208 --> 01:03:56.750
- Ouch.
- It's his fault. not ours!

1155
01:03:56.833 --> 01:03:59.625
Liar! Betrayer! Coward!

1156
01:03:59.708 --> 01:04:00.958
Leave! Now!

1157
01:04:01.833 --> 01:04:02.791
I'm so sorry.

1158
01:04:02.875 --> 01:04:03.875
You've done enough!

1159
01:04:04.916 --> 01:04:06.875
No!

1160
01:04:19.875 --> 01:04:23.541
Tear this place apart
until you find my son!

1161
01:04:51.916 --> 01:04:52.958
No.

1162
01:05:07.041 --> 01:05:08.291
Don't leave me.

1163
01:05:11.666 --> 01:05:12.791
Please.

1164
01:05:41.833 --> 01:05:44.083
Oh. I'll take that.

1165
01:05:44.166 --> 01:05:45.166
Thanks. kiddo.

1166
01:05:51.666 --> 01:05:54.125
Shoot. I left the. um… That. uh…

1167
01:05:54.208 --> 01:05:55.750
I know what it is. Be right back.

1168
01:05:55.833 --> 01:05:57.250
Thank you.

1169
01:06:15.458 --> 01:06:16.875
You couldn't find it. huh?

1170
01:06:16.958 --> 01:06:18.250
Would you toss me those?

1171
01:06:38.291 --> 01:06:39.375
Come on!

1172
01:06:40.041 --> 01:06:41.416
Stupid flashlight!

1173
01:06:43.708 --> 01:06:45.000
Sorry.

1174
01:06:48.875 --> 01:06:50.125
Are you okay?

1175
01:06:50.208 --> 01:06:52.458
No. I feel crazy!

1176
01:06:52.541 --> 01:06:53.583
I'm on the beach

1177
01:06:53.666 --> 01:06:57.000
trying to make contact
with I don't know what.

1178
01:07:00.208 --> 01:07:01.208
I just…

1179
01:07:03.333 --> 01:07:04.541
feel so…

1180
01:07:06.125 --> 01:07:07.125
alone.

1181
01:07:09.375 --> 01:07:11.041
You wouldn't understand.

1182
01:07:22.125 --> 01:07:23.125
Actually.

1183
01:07:24.625 --> 01:07:25.791
I do.

1184
01:07:58.666 --> 01:08:00.083
Oh.

1185
01:08:04.375 --> 01:08:06.333
I didn't think you'd miss me.

1186
01:08:07.875 --> 01:08:09.250
I missed you.

1187
01:08:10.291 --> 01:08:13.083
I've missed everything about you.

1188
01:08:13.958 --> 01:08:15.250
But…

1189
01:08:15.958 --> 01:08:18.375
this isn't the life you wanted.

1190
01:08:21.458 --> 01:08:23.166
The only thing I want

1191
01:08:24.166 --> 01:08:25.166
is you.

1192
01:08:40.583 --> 01:08:42.333
<i>Tía </i>Olga! Oh.

1193
01:08:42.416 --> 01:08:44.541
Oh. hey. you're back!

1194
01:08:44.625 --> 01:08:45.666
Whew.

1195
01:08:45.750 --> 01:08:47.750
Something's going on at the base.

1196
01:08:59.958 --> 01:09:02.416
Wait. That's my spaceship.

1197
01:09:02.500 --> 01:09:04.208
-Glordon's in there!
-Who?

1198
01:09:04.291 --> 01:09:05.625
My friend.

1199
01:09:05.708 --> 01:09:07.375
-You made a friend?
-You made a friend? Nice.

1200
01:09:07.458 --> 01:09:10.125
Yeah. and he needs our help.
You have clearance. right?

1201
01:09:10.208 --> 01:09:11.666
Not for this.

1202
01:09:12.166 --> 01:09:14.833
There's got to be
some way to get in there.

1203
01:09:14.916 --> 01:09:16.125
O-Okay. okay. Let me think.

1204
01:09:20.000 --> 01:09:21.333
Well. if you don't need me anymore.

1205
01:09:21.416 --> 01:09:23.458
I will begin my decomposition process.

1206
01:09:23.541 --> 01:09:25.000
Feel free to spread me over a plant

1207
01:09:25.083 --> 01:09:26.375
as nutritious fertilizer.

1208
01:09:30.041 --> 01:09:31.208
Wait!

1209
01:09:37.791 --> 01:09:39.375
They. uh. mention what it is?

1210
01:09:39.458 --> 01:09:42.416
Negative. But AARO's here
and NASA's on the way.

1211
01:09:44.458 --> 01:09:46.666
Is it extraterrestrial?

1212
01:09:46.750 --> 01:09:48.833
What. like little green men?

1213
01:09:48.916 --> 01:09:50.583
Don't tell me you believe in that stuff.

1214
01:09:54.083 --> 01:09:55.291
Who's there?

1215
01:09:58.916 --> 01:10:00.083
It's a kid.

1216
01:10:00.166 --> 01:10:01.375
Hey. you shouldn't be here.

1217
01:10:06.083 --> 01:10:08.208
Can you help me?

1218
01:10:18.625 --> 01:10:19.833
Huh?

1219
01:10:19.916 --> 01:10:22.708
I don't feel so good.

1220
01:10:24.291 --> 01:10:26.083
Get it off me!

1221
01:10:26.166 --> 01:10:27.500
Get it off me!

1222
01:10:30.166 --> 01:10:31.416
It's in my mouth!

1223
01:10:31.500 --> 01:10:32.458
Why is it sour?

1224
01:10:32.541 --> 01:10:33.666
It's on me too!

1225
01:10:33.750 --> 01:10:35.250
Help! Help!

1226
01:10:39.208 --> 01:10:40.708
Thank you for your service.

1227
01:11:24.958 --> 01:11:26.375
Glordon!

1228
01:11:32.916 --> 01:11:34.666
Is that your friend?

1229
01:11:35.250 --> 01:11:36.416
Elio?

1230
01:11:36.500 --> 01:11:38.750
What are you doing here?

1231
01:11:39.375 --> 01:11:40.625
What are you doing here?

1232
01:11:40.708 --> 01:11:42.458
Why didn't you stay where I told you?

1233
01:11:42.541 --> 01:11:43.791
I'm sorry.

1234
01:11:43.875 --> 01:11:47.208
I accidentally
turned on the ship.

1235
01:11:51.916 --> 01:11:53.666
Glordon? Glordon!

1236
01:11:53.750 --> 01:11:55.666
-Is he sick?
-His disc is broken.

1237
01:11:55.750 --> 01:11:57.083
It's too cold for him here!

1238
01:11:57.166 --> 01:11:58.250
Hey!

1239
01:11:58.333 --> 01:12:00.958
Put your hands up!
Back away from the specimen.

1240
01:12:02.541 --> 01:12:04.750
I said. back away! Now!

1241
01:12:04.833 --> 01:12:07.833
Shmeegle shmarpie blop.

1242
01:12:07.916 --> 01:12:10.083
You learned Elioese?

1243
01:12:13.916 --> 01:12:14.833
Hey. what are you saying?

1244
01:12:19.041 --> 01:12:20.958
-Oh. you mean "glöp."
-Stop that!

1245
01:12:24.375 --> 01:12:25.416
Gun it!

1246
01:12:46.000 --> 01:12:48.125
Oh. my gosh. Oh…

1247
01:12:48.625 --> 01:12:50.000
This is so…

1248
01:12:50.083 --> 01:12:50.916
Oh. my gosh.

1249
01:12:51.916 --> 01:12:53.000
Hold on. Glordon.

1250
01:12:53.083 --> 01:12:54.625
Olga. you got to drive!

1251
01:12:54.708 --> 01:12:56.208
-B-But how?
-Please!

1252
01:12:56.750 --> 01:12:58.166
<i>Welcome. guest pilot!</i>

1253
01:13:00.541 --> 01:13:01.708
Give me your jacket.

1254
01:13:03.375 --> 01:13:06.416
I'm so sorry. Glordon.
This is all my fault.

1255
01:13:09.291 --> 01:13:10.583
Don't worry.

1256
01:13:10.666 --> 01:13:12.083
I'm going to get you home.

1257
01:13:13.333 --> 01:13:14.833
Ship. get us to the Communiverse.

1258
01:13:16.333 --> 01:13:17.791
<i>Hyper-speed unavailable.</i>

1259
01:13:17.875 --> 01:13:18.708
<i>path blocked.</i>

1260
01:13:18.791 --> 01:13:20.625
What? It's totally clear.

1261
01:13:20.708 --> 01:13:22.791
<i>I said. "Hyper-speed unavailable.</i>

1262
01:13:22.875 --> 01:13:23.875
<i>path blocked."</i>

1263
01:13:23.958 --> 01:13:24.958
Oh. come on!

1264
01:13:31.625 --> 01:13:32.625
-What?
-Shh.

1265
01:13:37.333 --> 01:13:38.875
We're in a debris field.

1266
01:13:39.916 --> 01:13:41.833
-Let's just get out of here.
-No!

1267
01:13:42.708 --> 01:13:44.083
These objects are faster than bullets.

1268
01:13:44.166 --> 01:13:45.500
But this is what you do.

1269
01:13:45.583 --> 01:13:46.916
From the ground.

1270
01:13:47.000 --> 01:13:48.666
I don't know where
the debris's coming from.

1271
01:13:48.750 --> 01:13:50.625
I-I need altitudes. velo…

1272
01:13:50.708 --> 01:13:54.166
If I could just
contact someone on the ground.

1273
01:13:54.250 --> 01:13:56.208
But the base is on lockdown.

1274
01:13:56.291 --> 01:13:58.791
Maybe someone with a-- with a ham radio.

1275
01:13:58.875 --> 01:13:59.875
I don't know!

1276
01:14:01.291 --> 01:14:02.291
Elio?

1277
01:14:03.125 --> 01:14:05.458
Bro. I bet that UFO was real.

1278
01:14:06.041 --> 01:14:07.708
Oh. what if they're here for food

1279
01:14:07.791 --> 01:14:09.541
and the only thing they eat are hamsters?

1280
01:14:10.166 --> 01:14:11.291
I'm fine with that.

1281
01:14:19.541 --> 01:14:21.791
<i>PXLOL. please respond.</i>

1282
01:14:21.875 --> 01:14:23.166
<i>PXLOL. come in!</i>

1283
01:14:23.250 --> 01:14:25.166
Hello? This is PXLOL.

1284
01:14:25.250 --> 01:14:26.666
Bryce! Uh…

1285
01:14:26.750 --> 01:14:28.708
This is Elio.

1286
01:14:29.541 --> 01:14:32.125
<i>Solís</i>?
<i>I'm sorry about what happened.</i>

1287
01:14:32.208 --> 01:14:34.541
Caleb can be a real butt sometimes.

1288
01:14:34.625 --> 01:14:37.833
It's okay. I was a butt too.

1289
01:14:38.458 --> 01:14:40.250
Look. you might not believe this.

1290
01:14:40.333 --> 01:14:41.416
but we're in an alien ship that just…

1291
01:14:41.500 --> 01:14:42.833
That's you? Aw. man!

1292
01:14:42.916 --> 01:14:44.458
There's a lot of radio chatter about that.

1293
01:14:44.541 --> 01:14:45.375
<i>Yeah. that's us.</i>

1294
01:14:45.458 --> 01:14:46.666
<i>We're trying to fly through debris.</i>

1295
01:14:46.750 --> 01:14:48.208
but we need to know where it's coming…

1296
01:14:49.208 --> 01:14:51.083
How's your math? Physics?
Are you good at physics?

1297
01:14:51.166 --> 01:14:52.041
Whoa. Uh…

1298
01:14:52.125 --> 01:14:55.125
Bryce. I really need your help.

1299
01:14:55.208 --> 01:14:56.458
<i>Please.</i>

1300
01:14:56.541 --> 01:14:58.625
I don't know anything about debris.

1301
01:14:59.166 --> 01:15:00.666
but I know someone who does.

1302
01:15:00.750 --> 01:15:03.375
<i>He's a legend in my radio group.</i>

1303
01:15:03.458 --> 01:15:06.375
<i>The boss. The eyes in the sky. He's…</i>

1304
01:15:06.458 --> 01:15:09.083
Melmac reporting for duty!

1305
01:15:09.166 --> 01:15:11.250
I'll take it from here. PXLOL!

1306
01:15:11.333 --> 01:15:13.875
Elio. you better come back
in one piece. okay?

1307
01:15:13.958 --> 01:15:15.041
I'll tell you all about it.

1308
01:15:15.125 --> 01:15:17.375
Thank you. Melmac. I owe you a huge…

1309
01:15:17.458 --> 01:15:18.541
<i>Never mind that. Major.</i>

1310
01:15:18.625 --> 01:15:21.500
A Master of Ham always helps in a jam.

1311
01:15:21.583 --> 01:15:22.416
Ha!

1312
01:15:22.500 --> 01:15:24.500
Let's get you through this debris field.

1313
01:15:24.583 --> 01:15:25.583
I'm pulling up the network now.

1314
01:15:25.666 --> 01:15:26.500
Get ready.

1315
01:15:26.583 --> 01:15:27.958
We need a fixed target.

1316
01:15:28.041 --> 01:15:29.208
Orion's belt.

1317
01:15:29.291 --> 01:15:30.791
Perfect. Drive straight toward it.

1318
01:15:30.875 --> 01:15:32.250
- and be ready to dodge.
- Okay.

1319
01:15:32.333 --> 01:15:35.166
Uh. ship. can you. um--
can you project a grid?

1320
01:15:36.000 --> 01:15:38.375
Okay. Melmac. anything out there?

1321
01:15:38.458 --> 01:15:40.083
Hurry. before we're out of range!

1322
01:15:40.166 --> 01:15:42.208
Uh… Okay. Large rocket body!

1323
01:15:42.291 --> 01:15:43.875
Altitude. 407 kilometers.

1324
01:15:43.958 --> 01:15:45.333
<i>velocity. 7.66.</i>

1325
01:15:45.416 --> 01:15:46.416
Got it.

1326
01:15:46.500 --> 01:15:47.333
There.

1327
01:15:47.416 --> 01:15:48.500
Where? I-I don't see it!

1328
01:15:48.583 --> 01:15:49.750
Just pull back. Now!

1329
01:15:52.000 --> 01:15:55.416
Another one! 788 kilometers.
velocity. 7.46.

1330
01:15:55.500 --> 01:15:57.375
-Climb fast! Now!
-Roger!

1331
01:15:59.041 --> 01:16:00.916
Whoo! We are going ham!

1332
01:16:02.125 --> 01:16:03.166
You're doing great.

1333
01:16:03.250 --> 01:16:04.291
Melmac. keep them coming.

1334
01:16:04.375 --> 01:16:06.125
Major. you're leaving the comm window.

1335
01:16:06.208 --> 01:16:07.291
Just stay on this frequency.

1336
01:16:07.833 --> 01:16:09.375
<i>Stay… frequency…</i>

1337
01:16:09.458 --> 01:16:11.250
Melmac? Melmac?

1338
01:16:13.791 --> 01:16:16.166
<i>Shields at 80%.</i>

1339
01:16:18.666 --> 01:16:19.666
Glordon.

1340
01:16:20.250 --> 01:16:21.333
Is anyone there?

1341
01:16:21.416 --> 01:16:24.416
Please. anyone? Mayday!
Mayday! Come in. Come in!

1342
01:16:27.083 --> 01:16:29.000
<i>Shields at 60%.</i>

1343
01:16:36.791 --> 01:16:38.916
<i>Shields at 41%.</i>

1344
01:16:44.000 --> 01:16:45.708
<i>Shields at 23%.</i>

1345
01:16:45.791 --> 01:16:48.625
Mayday! Mayday! Come in. Come in!

1346
01:16:48.708 --> 01:16:50.625
- Hello?
<i>- Shields at 16%.</i>

1347
01:16:51.666 --> 01:16:53.750
Is anyone out there?

1348
01:16:53.833 --> 01:16:55.291
Can anyone hear us?

1349
01:17:09.125 --> 01:17:11.125
<i>This is…</i>

1350
01:17:11.208 --> 01:17:12.333
<i>…Senegal.</i>

1351
01:17:14.500 --> 01:17:16.791
<i>Bonjour. This is</i>
<i>Masters of Ham in Senegal.</i>

1352
01:17:16.875 --> 01:17:18.416
Yes. yes. We read you.

1353
01:17:18.500 --> 01:17:21.166
<i>Large debris</i>
<i>at 1.300 kilometers.</i>

1354
01:17:21.250 --> 01:17:23.041
<i>velocity. 7.2.</i>

1355
01:17:23.125 --> 01:17:24.791
Pull back! Hard!

1356
01:17:26.333 --> 01:17:27.291
Thank you. Thank you.

1357
01:17:27.375 --> 01:17:28.916
<i>Masters</i>
<i>of Ham at your service.</i>

1358
01:17:29.000 --> 01:17:30.500
<i>This is Giulia from Italia.</i>

1359
01:17:30.583 --> 01:17:31.958
This is awesome!

1360
01:17:32.041 --> 01:17:34.000
-<i>2.224. velocity 6.81.</i>
-Right.

1361
01:17:35.000 --> 01:17:36.333
<i>This is Anoush in Armenia.</i>

1362
01:17:36.416 --> 01:17:38.166
-<i>Velocity. 6.75.</i>
-Right!

1363
01:17:38.250 --> 01:17:39.291
<i>Namaste.</i>

1364
01:17:39.375 --> 01:17:40.666
-<i>This is Vikram from Mumbai.</i>
-Climb!

1365
01:17:40.750 --> 01:17:42.750
<i>Debris at 2.753.</i>

1366
01:17:42.833 --> 01:17:44.958
-<i>velocity. 6.61.</i>
-Left!

1367
01:17:45.041 --> 01:17:47.208
<i>-This is Hoang in Vietnam.</i>
<i>-Velocity 6…</i>

1368
01:17:47.291 --> 01:17:48.708
<i>Konnichiwa from Japan.</i>

1369
01:17:48.791 --> 01:17:50.000
<i>You can do this!</i>

1370
01:17:50.083 --> 01:17:52.250
-<i>You're going to be okay.</i>
-<i>You're not alone.</i>

1371
01:17:52.333 --> 01:17:53.666
- <i>Go. go. go!</i>
<i>- Come on. kid!</i>

1372
01:17:53.750 --> 01:17:55.375
-<i>Keep going!</i>
-<i>You're almost there!</i>

1373
01:17:57.791 --> 01:17:59.291
<i>There's one more piece!</i>

1374
01:17:59.375 --> 01:18:00.416
<i>Move. move. move!</i>

1375
01:18:00.500 --> 01:18:01.375
-Which way?
-I don't know.

1376
01:18:17.291 --> 01:18:18.291
<i>Path cleared.</i>

1377
01:18:31.750 --> 01:18:33.416
Glordon?

1378
01:18:37.375 --> 01:18:39.000
<i>Engaging hyper-speed.</i>

1379
01:19:05.750 --> 01:19:07.583
Help us. Please.

1380
01:19:08.458 --> 01:19:09.875
- Elio.
- Glordon. No!

1381
01:19:09.958 --> 01:19:11.625
Get off me!

1382
01:19:24.000 --> 01:19:25.000
Glordon.

1383
01:19:26.500 --> 01:19:27.666
Glordon. wake up.

1384
01:19:31.875 --> 01:19:32.875
No.

1385
01:19:33.875 --> 01:19:35.375
I can't lose you too.

1386
01:19:43.000 --> 01:19:44.458
No!

1387
01:20:49.791 --> 01:20:51.833
Explain yourselves.

1388
01:20:54.166 --> 01:20:55.166
Huh?

1389
01:20:55.250 --> 01:20:57.750
I-- I can't.

1390
01:20:57.833 --> 01:20:59.500
Just tell him.

1391
01:21:00.166 --> 01:21:01.750
He loves you.

1392
01:21:02.333 --> 01:21:04.208
Look how much he wanted you back.

1393
01:21:08.791 --> 01:21:09.791
I-I…

1394
01:21:10.583 --> 01:21:13.250
I don't want to be a war machine.

1395
01:21:18.833 --> 01:21:20.208
You already know?

1396
01:21:21.083 --> 01:21:22.083
Yes.

1397
01:21:24.000 --> 01:21:27.166
I may not always understand you.

1398
01:21:28.791 --> 01:21:30.500
but I still love you.

1399
01:21:38.500 --> 01:21:40.791
It's a loose swaddle.

1400
01:21:40.875 --> 01:21:43.000
I do not have your mother's touch.

1401
01:21:43.083 --> 01:21:44.333
You did great.

1402
01:21:46.541 --> 01:21:49.833
I have never uttered these words before.

1403
01:21:50.916 --> 01:21:52.500
but I am…

1404
01:21:52.583 --> 01:21:54.750
…sorry.

1405
01:21:56.416 --> 01:21:57.500
Release them all.

1406
01:22:24.333 --> 01:22:27.750
Congratulations.
Ambassador Solís!

1407
01:22:29.541 --> 01:22:31.583
But I-I lied to you!

1408
01:22:31.666 --> 01:22:35.291
And then you sacrificed
yourself to save another.

1409
01:22:35.916 --> 01:22:40.291
You behaved as admirably
as any real planetary leader.

1410
01:22:40.375 --> 01:22:42.041
And you did bring peace.

1411
01:22:42.625 --> 01:22:43.791
Eventually.

1412
01:22:43.875 --> 01:22:45.875
You have earned your place here.

1413
01:22:46.458 --> 01:22:47.541
I could stay?

1414
01:22:47.625 --> 01:22:49.291
Yes. yes. yes!

1415
01:22:52.458 --> 01:22:54.166
Excellent.

1416
01:22:55.166 --> 01:22:56.416
We can hang out every day.

1417
01:23:58.458 --> 01:24:00.291
This place is amazing.

1418
01:24:00.791 --> 01:24:03.125
but Earth is…

1419
01:24:04.750 --> 01:24:05.750
home.

1420
01:24:07.041 --> 01:24:08.708
I didn't give it a chance. but…

1421
01:24:10.416 --> 01:24:11.416
now…

1422
01:24:12.958 --> 01:24:13.958
I want to try.

1423
01:24:19.625 --> 01:24:20.625
With you.

1424
01:24:25.125 --> 01:24:26.291
Are you sure?

1425
01:24:29.000 --> 01:24:30.000
We're family.

1426
01:24:40.250 --> 01:24:41.541
This isn't goodbye.

1427
01:24:42.041 --> 01:24:44.458
It's just not yet.

1428
01:24:47.458 --> 01:24:48.625
We understand.

1429
01:24:50.375 --> 01:24:53.541
You are unique. Elio of Earth.

1430
01:24:53.625 --> 01:24:57.375
and "unique" can sometimes
feel like "alone."

1431
01:24:58.750 --> 01:25:01.083
But you are not alone.

1432
01:25:04.916 --> 01:25:05.916
Okay.

1433
01:25:06.416 --> 01:25:07.416
Bye.

1434
01:25:07.958 --> 01:25:08.958
I love you.

1435
01:25:15.333 --> 01:25:18.416
Okay. Bye. I love you.

1436
01:25:18.500 --> 01:25:20.583
Okay. Bye. I love you.

1437
01:25:22.833 --> 01:25:24.916
Okay. Bye. I love you.

1438
01:25:39.250 --> 01:25:40.250
I love you. too.

1439
01:25:51.000 --> 01:25:52.000
Let's go home.

1440
01:26:32.125 --> 01:26:34.000
<i>It's an ancient human theme.</i>

1441
01:26:34.083 --> 01:26:36.000
<i>You can find it</i>
<i>in virtually every culture.</i>

1442
01:26:36.083 --> 01:26:38.416
<i>In. uh. religion. folklore. superstition.</i>

1443
01:26:38.500 --> 01:26:39.833
<i>and. now. in science.</i>

1444
01:26:41.250 --> 01:26:45.541
<i>The search for life elsewhere</i>
<i>is remarkable in our age</i>

1445
01:26:46.083 --> 01:26:47.458
<i>because this is the first time</i>

1446
01:26:47.541 --> 01:26:50.750
<i>that we can actually do</i>
<i>something besides speculation.</i>

1447
01:26:56.500 --> 01:26:59.250
<i>We can send spacecraft to nearby planets.</i>

1448
01:27:00.791 --> 01:27:02.833
<i>We can use large radio telescopes to see</i>

1449
01:27:02.916 --> 01:27:05.916
<i>if there is any message</i>
<i>being sent to us lately.</i>

1450
01:27:08.333 --> 01:27:12.000
<i>And it touches to</i>
<i>the deepest of human concerns.</i>

1451
01:27:12.875 --> 01:27:13.916
<i>Are we alone?</i>

1452
01:29:41.291 --> 01:29:43.458
Glordon. your disc is muted.

1453
01:29:43.541 --> 01:29:44.625
<i>Oops. sorry.</i>

1454
01:29:44.708 --> 01:29:47.625
<i>Now. tell me everything.</i>

